\id LUK - - Nama Back Translation
\c 1
\s Opening talk
\p
\v 1 Friend Tiafilus:
\p
Many people made a plan to write what had happen to us. \v 2 They did from what talk had seen in the beginning and who wrote it. \v 3 I have carefully looked for all things from the beginning, it seemed good to me to write what had exactly happened. I have done for you very good, Tiafilus, \v 4 I do this so that you will know all true talk which you have heard.
\s Annoucement of his birth of Jon the Baptist
\p
\v 5 At that time of when Erod was the ruling man(king) of Judia there was burning sacrifice men name Jakaraya who belonged in the group of burning sacrifice men Abia, his wife Elisafet (was) a descendant of Eron. \v 6 Jakaraya and Elisafet lived in good life in the sight of God, they followed all the Lord's law. \v 7 But they.d lived without a baby because Elisafet was barren, and they.d became old.
\p
\v 8 One day it came to Jakaraya's family's turn of the burning sacrifice man work, and he started woking to burn sacrifice before God,{l{
\f...f* {l{1.8 
One day it came to turn Jakaraya's burning sacrifice men work before God. 
it need to check again.

 \v 9 According to their custom, God chose him to burn thing with good smell in the worshipping house of God. \v 10 When the day came to burn sacrifice, all the people gathered in the place of the worshipping house to talk with God(talking with God).
\p
\v 11 Then an heaven talk carrying man(man carrying heavenly message) of God appeared to him, and stood at the right side from the table burning sacrifice(altar). \v 12 When Jakaraya saw him, he was surprised and was full of fear. \v 13 But the man carrying heavenly message said to him, "Don't be afraid, Jakaraya, he (God) heard your talking with God. Your wife Elisafet will bear a son, you must give name him Jon. \v 14 He will be joy and happiness for you, and many [people] will rejoice because of his birth. \v 15 He will be big in God's eye, (and he will be) wihout-drink alcohol and other strong drink, and he will be full of the God Spirit from the birth. \v 16 He will turn many people from of Israil(Israil people) to the Lord to their God. \v 17 And he will go ahead of Lord, in the spirit and in the power like Elaija was, in order to turn father's heart to their children and without-hearing(disobedient) life to the wisdom; he prepare true life for the Lord.
\p
\v 18 Jakaya asked the man carrying heavenly message, "How can I become knowing(know) about this? I am an old man and my wife is also old woman."
\p
\v 19 The man carrying heavenly message answered, "I am Geibrèl. I stand close to God and he sent me with talk [which] I will tell you this good talk. \v 20 And now silence put [into] you and [you] cannot speak until the practicing day come because you didn't become true(believe) my talk. Which [it] will come true in its day.
\p
\v 21 In this long time when the people were waiting for Zakaraya and was confusing mind(wondering) because he was staying very long [time] in the worshipping house. \v 22 When he came out, he couldn't say anything to them. They realized that he had seen a eye passover thing in the worshipping house, he became without-talk(couldn't speak) them (but) only with hands made surprising things (to them). \v 23 When his worshipping days were finished, he went back to home. \v 24 After (this) his wife became pregnant and for 5 months she stayed only inside house [but] she didn't go out. \v 25 Elisabet said, "The Lord did it for me, in this day God showed his favor and took away my shameful things from the people!"
\s Report about the Birth of Yesu
\p
\v 26 In the 6th month of Elijafet's [pregnancy], God sent the man carrying heavenly message Geibrèl to Najaret in Galili region region, \v 27 to the pure girl(the girl without relationship with man) whom did without.lying talk(promise) to marry with Josef, in the family of Defid, her name was Meri. \v 28 The man carrying heavenly message came Meri and said, "Blessed with talkǃ The Lord is with you." \v 29 Meri was so surprised of his talks and wondered how this greeting will be. \v 30 But the man carrying heavenly message said to her, "Don't be afraid, Meri, you have found God's favor. \v 31 You will be with a son and be pregnant a son, and you must give the name Yesu. \v 32 He will be big and will be called the son of the Most High. The Lord God will make him the ruling man(king) as his ancester Deifid was. \v 33 And he will be a ruler people of Israil forever. His kingdom will never end."
\p
\v 34 Meri asked the man carrying heavenly message, "How will be this, because I am virgin?"
\p
\v 35 The man carrying heavenly message answered, " Surely, the God Spirit will come to you, and the power of Most High will cover you. The without.dust(holy) son will be called God's son. \v 36 Elisafet, your relative will be with child in her old age, and [she] who was said the barren is 6th month now. \v 37 Because there are no hard for God."
\p
\v 38 Meri answered, "I am the God's without.payment working man(servant). It will happen what you told me." After talks the man carrying heavenly message left her.
\p
\s Meri visits Elisafet
\p
\v 39 At that day Meri got quickly prepared and (went) to a town in the mountain side in Judia. \v 40 She went into Jakaraya's house and gave greeting to Elisabet. \v 41 When Elisabet heard Meri's greeting, the baby moved in her belly and Elisabet was filled with God Spirit. \v 42 She spoke a loudly, "Blessed are you among women, and blessed is the child you will bearǃ \v 43 Why am I favored, the mother of my Lord comes to me? \v 44 When your greeting was heard, the baby in my belly moved with joy. \v 45 How happy is she who responds what God's ture talk will be done to her.
\s Meri's Song
\p
\v 46 Meri said, "My heart praises the Lord
\q1 \v 47 and my spirit rejoices in God my saving man,
\q1 \v 48 for he remembers me (as )his humble without.payment working man(servant) woman. From now on all the people will call me you are blessed.
\q1 \v 49 for the power of Most High has done surprised thing for me. His name is without.dust(holy).
\q1 \v 50 His mercy will extend to those who fear Him from generation to generation.
\q1 \v 51 He has shown mighty with his hands; he scattered those who are high-mind.
\q1 \v 52 He put down rulers from their positions, but has raised up the humble.
\q1 \v 53 He has filled the hungry with many things, but has sent the rich empty.
\q1 \v 54 He has helped his without.payment working man(servant) Israil, remebering with mercy.
\q1 \v 55 to Ebraam and his descendants forever how he had said to our fathers.
\q1 \v 56 Meri stayed with Elisafet for three months after Meri went back village.
\s The birth of Jon the baptist
\p
\v 57 When the time for Elisafet to have her baby, she gave birth to a son. \v 58 Her neighbors and relatives heard that God has shown big mercy and they rejoiced with her.
\p
\v 59 On the eighth day they went to circumcise the child, and they were going to name(gave a name)him after his father Jakaraya, \v 60 but his mother said, "Noǃ his name will be Jon."
\p
\v 61 They said, "There is no one among your relatives who has that name."
\p
\v 62 They made a surprising thing with hand to his father to [find out what] he give son's name. \v 63 He asked for a writing paper with surprising thing by hand, and every people was surprised that he wrote, "His name is Jon." \v 64 Immediately Jakaraya started saying and praising God. \v 65 The neighbors were filled with fear, and Judia people were talking about these things. \v 66 Everyone who heard this were wondered and asking, "Who is this child going to be?" For Lord's hand was there.
\s Jakaraya's song
\p
\v 67 His fatherJakaraya was filled with spirit and began to speak,
\q \v 68 "Praise be to the Lord, the God of Israil,
\q2 who has come to save his people.
\q \v 69 He has sent us saving man
\q2 in his without.payment working man(servant) Deifid his family.
\q1 \v 70 What he said through his God's people who make know(prophets) of long ago,
\q1 \v 71 salvation from our enemies
\q2 and from hand of all who hate us.
\q1 \v 72 he showed mercy to our fathers and remembered his without.dust(holy) covenant.
\q1 \v 73 He said without changing talk/oath to our father Ebraam.
\q2 \v 74 He rescued us from our enemies's hand
\q2 and enabled us to serve him without fear.
\q1 \v 75 In holiness and straightness before God all our days.
\q1 \v 76 You, my child, will be be a God's man who make know(prophet) of the Most High,
\q2 you will be(go) before Lord to prepare the way for him,
\q1 \v 77 you will give his people the knowledge of salvation
\q2 through the washing of their sins.
\q1 \v 78 Because of our God's mercy
\q2 from heaven the rising sunwill come to us.
\q1 \v 79 It will shine on those who lived in darkness
\q2 and on those who lived under death,
\q1 he will guide our feet into the path of peace.
\p
\v 80 The child grew and became strong in spirit, and he stayed in desert until he appeared publicly to Israil.
\c 2
\s The Birth of Yesu
\p
\v 1 In those days [Rom high ruling man] Kaisar Augustus gave strong talk widely to take a census(gave name to register) in Roman country. \v 2 This was the first thing to take a census when Kwirinius was governor in Siria. \v 3 All people went to their town to take a census.
\p
\v 4 So, because Josef was descendant of Deifid, he went from the town of Najaret in Galili region region to Betliem in Judia, that town was where Deifid grew up. \v 5 He went there with Meri to register the name, who had said to marry to(was engaged with) Josef and almost gave birth a child. \v 6 While they.d were there, the day came near to gave birth child, \v 7 and she gave birth to first head(firstborn) son. She wrapped the son with clothes and placed him in a animal's food container(manger) because there was no space(room) for them in the house.
\s The watching men of sheep and the men carrying heavenly message(angels)
\p
\v 8 And watching men of sheep were living in the near fields, they watched sheep at night. \v 9 An man carrying heavenly message of the Lord suddenly appeared to them, and the big light(glory) of the Lord shone, they were afraid. \v 10 But the man carrying heavenly message said to them, "Don't be afraid. I bring good talk to you big joy to all the people. \v 11 Today in the town of Deifid, Savior was born for you; he is the Lord Keriso. \v 12 This is recognising for you: you will find a child wrapped with clothes in a animal's food container(manger)."
\p
\v 13 Suddenly so many men carrying heavenly message(angels) appeared with the man carrying heavenly message, praising God and said,
\q1 \v 14 "Glory to God in very high,
\q2 on land peace is to them to his liking people."
\p
\v 15 When the men carrying heavenly message(angels) left them and went to heaven, the watching men of sheep said to on another, "Let's go to Betliem to see what has happened there, which the Lord has told us about." \v 16 They went quickly and found Meri, Josef, and the baby who was lying in an animal's container. \v 17 When they saw him, they spread the talk about the child what man carrying heavenly message had told them. \v 18 All who heard it were amazed at what the watching men of sheep told to them. \v 19 Meri had the talk in her heart and keep remembering them. \v 20 The watching men of sheep went back with praising God with joy because what they heard and seen in the eye, just as they told to them.
\s Yesu was in the worshipping house
\p
\v 21 On the eighth day, the day came to cut his skin(circumcise him), his name Yesu, [which]the man carrying heavenly message had firstly given him before he was conceived.
\p
\v 22 When the day came cleaning feast doing how the law of Moses was, Josef and Meri brought the child to Jeusalem to present to the Lord, \v 23 how how [he] wrote the law of the Lord, "Every firstborn son is to present to the Lord." \v 24 And they went to present a sacrifice because how the law of the Lord said to [take] two of doves o two young pigeons.
\s The report of Saimon
\p
\v 25 There was a man in Jerusalem name Saimon, who was straight and God-fearing man. He was waiting for salvation of Israil, and he was full of God Spirit. \v 26 The God Spirit gave a plan to him that, 'You will not die before you will see the Lord's Keriso.' \v 27 The God Spirit led the Saimon into the worshipping house. When his parents brought there the child Yesu to do what the custom of the law were, \v 28 Saimon took child with his hands and return God joyfully God and saying,
\q1 \v 29 "Savior Lord, what you have said me,
\q2 now I, your worker can die with joy.
\q1 \v 30 Because my eyes have seen your salvation,
\q2 \v 31 so that all people will see which you have prepared.
\q2 \v 32 He will be like a light that show your truth to Side people,
\q2 and he will cause people to think highly the people of Israil.
\p
\v 33 The child's father and mother were surprised what had said about him. \v 34 Saimon blessed them and said to Meri, his mother, "This child will cause some Israil people to stop believing God, and many to turn to God, and he will be a surprising thing to warn people but many people will be against him. \v 35 So [that] the evil thoughts from many people's hearts will be revealed. Doing to bad things they will do to him will give you big sorrow."
\s Anna's report about life
\p
\v 36 There was a woman God's man who make know(prophet), Anna, the daughter of Fanuel of the family/clan of Aser. She was very old, and she lived with her husband only 7 years. \v 37 And [then] she became a widow until she became 84 years old. She never left the worshipping house but bent down/worshiped night and day, talked with God and fasted. \v 38 At that time she came to them, she gave thanks to God and spoke about the child to (all) who were waiting for salvation of Jerusalem.
\p
\v 39 When Josef and Meri had finished what the law of the Lord required, they.d returned to Galili region to their town of Najaret. \v 40 The child grew and became strong; he was full of wisdom, and the grace of God was to him.
\s The Boy Yesu at the worshipping house
\p
\v 41 In every year his parents went to Jerusalem to the feast of Passover. \v 42 When he became 12 years old, they went there the feast according to custom. \v 43 After the feast [was over], his parents were coming back hometown, the boy Yesu stayed in Jerusalem, but they.d didn't know about child. \v 44 They were thinking that he might return trip together, [and] they went on for a day. They began looking for him among their relatives and to friends. \v 45 When they didn't find him, they went back to Jerusalem looking for him. \v 46 After three days they found him in the worshipping house, sitting with the teaching men, listening to them and asking them questions. \v 47 Everyone who heard him they were amazed at his carrying bright thinking(undersanding) in his answers. \v 48 When his parents saw him, they were surprised. and his mother said, "Son, why are you doing like this to us? I with your father were painfully looking for you.
\p
\v 49 Yesu answered them, "Why were you looking for me? You should know that I am in my Father's house." \v 50 But they didn't understand what talk he was saying.
\p
\v 51 He went back to Najaret with parents and he became obedient man to the parents. But his mother accepted all talks in her heart. \v 52 Yesu grew in body and in wisdom and in favor with God and men.
\c 3
\s Jon the Baptist prepared the way
\p
\v 1 When Tiberius Emperor ruled Rom 15 years, when Fontius Failet was governor of Judia, Erod was ruler in Galili region, Erod's small brother Filif was ruler in Itulia and Trakonitis, and Lisanias was ruler in Abilene, \v 2 and at that time Anas and Kayafas were leading burning sacrifice men, God's talk came to Jon son of Jakaraya in the desert. \v 3 He went through all the region of Joden, he preached about baptism and baptized to turn away from sins. \v 4 How [someone] wrote it in the God's talk(is written in the talks of God/scripture), God's man who make know(prophet) Aisaya,
\q1 "Someone is shouting in the desert,
\q1 'To prepare the way for the Lord to travel,
\q2 making a straight paths for him.
\q1 \v 5 Every valley shall be smooth,
\q2 and every montain shall be leveled and lowered.
\q1 Every crooked roads shall be straight,
\q2 and the bad roads shall bestraighten.
\q1 \v 6 And all people will see God's salvation.'"
\p
\v 7 Jon said to the crowds which came to be baprtized by him, "You are the people with snack lifeǃ Who told you (people) to flee from God's anger? \v 8 You will do these things which you will show that you had turned from (your) sin. And do not try to say among youselves that, 'Ebraam is our ancester.' I tell you that out of these stones God can raise up children for Ebraam. \v 9 The ax is ready to cut the root of the trees, and if which tree does not bear fruits will be cut and thrown into the fire."
\p
\v 10 The crowd asked, "What shall we do from here?"
\p
\v 11 Jon answered, "If the man with two shirts must give it to other, and who has food must do the same way.
\p
\v 12 Tax collectors came the same way to be baptized, they asked, "Teacher, what should we do?"
\p
\v 13 He told them, "Don't collect with your wanting from what had told to." \v 14 Some soldiers also asked him, "What should we do?"
\p
He answered, "Don't steal money from people and accuse them with lying and be content with your pay.
\p
\v 15 The people were waiting with saying and were all wondering in their hearts that Jon might be the Keriso. \v 16 Jon answered them all, "I baptize you with water. But one who is coming whose power surpasses me, I cannot untie the thongs of his sandols. He will baptize you with the God Spirit and with fire. \v 17 He is ready to divide chaffs from the fruitful seeds with fork. Then he will sweep the place, will gather fruitful seeds into his house, but he will burn chaffs into the without-end fire. \v 18 And with many other talks Jon advised them and preached the good talk to them.
\p
\v 19 But when Jon rebuked the ruler Erod because of Erodias, his young brother's wife, and the other evil things he did, \v 20 Erod added this to them. He put Jon to the darkness house(darkness house).
\p
\s The Baptism of Yesu
\p
\v 21 When he baptized all the people, he also baptized Yesu. When he was talking with God, heaven was opened, \v 22 and the God Spirit came down to Yesu with a through bird like a mamu(pigeon). A voice came from heaven, "You are my lovely son, I'm so pleased with you."
\s Ancester of Yesu
\p
\v 23 Yesu himself was 30 years old when he began his work.
\q1 Yesu was thought widely that was the Josef's son,
\q2 Josef was the son of Eli,
\q1 \v 24 the Son of Matat, the son of Lefi, the son of Melki,
\q2 the son of Yanai, the Josef's son,
\q1 \v 25 the son of Matatias, the son of Amos,
\q2 the son of Nakum, the son of Esli, the son of Nagai,
\q1 \v 26 the son of Mat, the son of Matatias,
\q2 the son of Semein, the son of Josek, the son of Joda
\pi \v 27 the son of Joanan, the son of Resa,
\q2 the son of Jerufafel, the son of Sealtiel, the son of Neri,
\q1 \v 28 the son of Melki, the son of Adi,
\q2 the son of Kosam, the son of Elmadam, the son of Er,
\q1 \v 29 the son of Josua, the son of Elieser, the son of Jorim,
\q2 the son of Matat, the son of Lefi,
\q1 \v 30 the son of Saimon, the son of Juda,
\q2 the Josef's son, the son of Jonam, the son of Eliakim,
\q1 \v 31 the son of Melia, the son of Mena,
\q2 the son of Matata, the son of Natan, the son of Deifid,
\q1 \v 32 the son of Jesi, the son of Obed,
\q2 the son of Boas, the son of Samon, the son of Nasun,
\q1 \v 33 the son of Aminadaf, the son of Ram,
\q2 the son of Ejron, the son of Feres,
\q1 \v 34 the son of Jeikof, the son of Aisek,
\q2 the son of Ebraam, the son of Tera, the son of Naor,
\q1 \v 35 the son of Seruk, the son of Reu,
\q2 the son of Felek, the son of Efer, the son of Sela,
\q1 \v 36 the son of Keinan, the son of Afasad,
\q2 the son of Sem, the son of Noa, the son of Lamek,
\q1 \v 37 the son of Metusela, the son of Enok,
\q2 the son of Jared, the son of Maalalel, the son of Kenan,
\q1 \v 38 the son of Enos, the son of Set,
\q2 the son of Edèm, the son of God.
\c 4
\s The temptation of Yesu
\p
\v 1 Yesu, full of the God Spirit, returned from the Joden and the God Spirit led into the desert, \v 2 for the forty days Saifè tempted him. He did not eat during these days, after that he was hungry.
\p
\v 3 Sáifèr said, "If you are God's son, turn this stone into the food."
\p
\v 4 Yesu answered, "It is written in the God's talk, 'Man shall not live by food alone.'
\p
\v 5 Sáifèr led him to the mountain and showed him all the world. \v 6 Sáifèr said to him, "I will give you all the authority and good things, for [these] are mine, I will give it to anyone I want. \v 7 If you worship me, all will be yours."
\p
\v 8 Yesu answered, "It is written in the God's talk, 'Worship your Lord God and serve him only.'" \v 9 Sáifèr led him to Jerusalem and had him stand on the highest point of the worshipping house. He said, "If you are the son of God, jump to the land from here." \v 10 It is written in the talk of God that,
\q1 "He will send men carrying heavenly message(angels) to guard you,
\q1 \v 11 they will hold you with their hands
\q2 so that your foot will not be hurt on a stone.'
\p
\v 12 Yesu answered, "It says that, you don't put your Lord God into the test.'"
\p
\v 13 When Sáifèr finished his temptation, he left Yesu until other day.
\s They rejected Yesu at Najaret
\p
\v 14 Yesu went back to Galili region with the power of God Spirit, talk about him became wide through the whole area. \v 15 He taught them through their meeting houses(meeting houses), and every people praised him.
\p
\v 16 He went to Najaret, where he grew up, on the sabbath he went and entered into the meeting house as his custom was. He stood up to read. \v 17 They gave him the scroll book of the God's man who make know(prophet) Aisaya. He unrolled it[scroll] and he found the talks[it is] written,
\p
\v 18 "The Spirit of the Lord is on me, because he anointed me to teach good talk to the poor. He sent me to speak one who put in the darkness house saving, the blind will see, people with problem will be light \v 19 In this year the Lord's wanting happen."
\p
\v 20 Then he rolled up the scroll, gave it back to the meeting house keeper and sat down in the teaching place. Everyone's eyes in the worshipping house was looking at him. \v 21 He began to say to them, "Today this talk become true in your hearing.
\p
\v 22 All spoke well of him about blessing talk and were amazed at the good talk that came out from his lips. They asked, "This is the Josef's son."
\p
\v 23 Yesu said to them, "You will take this wise talk to me, 'Doctor, heal yourselfǃ' And you will tell me, 'Do here in your hometown what we have heard that you did in Kafernam."
\p
\v 24 He continued, "I will tell truth, all God's man who make know(prophet) don't be welcomed in his hometown. \v 25 I let you know that there are many widows in Israil in Elaija's day, when the sky shut down for three and half years. There was famine throughout land. \v 26 But Elaija was not sent to any of the Ju people, but to only a widow in Jarefat in Sidon. \v 27 There were many in Israil with leprosy[with skin disease] in the time of Elisa, yet not one of them was cleasend [but] only Naaman from the Siria.
\p
\v 28 All the people in the meeting house were angry when they heard this talks. \v 29 They got angry, drove him out of the town and hold him to the mountain where was the village, from there they tried to throw him off the hole/cliff. \v 30 But he walked through the people and went away.
\s1 Yesu drove/chased out an evil spirit
\p
\v 31 Then he went to Kafernam town in Galili region, and on the Safat he began to teach the people. \v 32 They were surprised of his teaching, because his teaching were with authority.
\p
\v 33 In the meeting house there was a man spoiled by evil spirit. He shouted at the very high. \v 34 "Haǃ What do you want with us, Yesu of Najaret? [Have] you came to destroy us? I know who are you. You are the Without.dust man of Godǃ"
\p
\v 35 Yesu ordered it, "Be guietǃ Come out of him." Then the evil spirit threw the man before[the eyes of] people and came out and left him without doing him [any] harm.
\p
\v 36 All the people were amazed and said to each other, "What teaching is this? With authority and power he ordered the evil spirits and they went outǃ" \v 37 And the talk about him became wide thoughout near town.
\s1 Yesu healed many people
\p
\v 38 Yesu left the meeting house and went to Saimon's house. Saimon's mother-in-law was sickness with a fever(cough), and they asked Yesu to help her. \v 39 He bent down to her and he told the sickness, "Move away!" and the sickness of fever left her. She got up immediately and cooked food for them. \v 40 When the sun was setting, the people brought to Yesu all who had various [kinds of] sickness, and he placed the hand on them, [and] healed them. \v 41 The evil spirit came out from many people, they shouted, "You are the Son of Godǃ" But Yesu stopped them speaking, because they knew that he was the Keriso. \v 42 At daybreak Yesu went to clear place. The people were looking for Yesu and when they came to where Yesu was, they stopped him(Yesu) not to leave them. \v 43 But he said, "I will(must) preach the good talk of the ruling of God to the other towns, because that's why he sent me." \v 44 He continued to preach in the meeting houses of Judia.
\c 5
\s1 Yesu called his first following men
\p
\v 1 One day Yesu was standing near the Lake of Genesaret, with group of people surrounding him and listening to the talk of God, \v 2 He saw two bouts at the side of water, left them.d there by the fishermen, who were washing their nets. \v 3 He got into one of the bouts, which was Saimon's, [and] said him to move the bouts littlebit [from the shore]. Then he sat down and began to teach the people from inside of the bout. \v 4 When he finished talk, he said to Saimon, "Take nets to the middle of water(deep water) and hang them for catching the fish." \v 5 Saimon answered, "Teacher, we worked all night and we didn't catch anything. But because you already said so, I will go to hang the nets."
\p
\v 6 When they did what he had told them, they caught many fish and their nets was about to break. \v 7 So they made a surprising thing to the friends in the other bout to help them, they came and put so many fish in the two bouts and they were about to sink.
\p
\v 8 When Saimon Fitè saw this, he bowed down to Yesu's knees and said, "Go away from me, Lord; I am a sinful manǃ" \v 9 He and all his helpers were astonised at catching of fish, \v 10 in a same way were Jems and Jon, the sons of Jebedi, Saimon's friends.
\p
Yesu said to Saimon, "Don't be afraid. From now on you will become catching men for many people." \v 11 They pulled their bouts to the shore, left everything and followed him.
\s1 Yesu healed a man with leprosy
\p
\v 12 While Yesu was in one of the town, a man [who] was with skin disease(leprosy). When he saw Yesu, he fell with his face to the ground and begged him, "Lord, if you want, you can make me clean."
\p
\v 13 Yesu reached out his hand and touched the man and said. "I really want to do. You will be cleanǃ" And immediately the leprocy left him.
\p
\v 14 Yesu told him, "Don't tell anyone, you must go, show yourself to the burning sacrifice man and offer the sacrifices that Moses told you for your healing so that people will see that your skin is good.
\p
\v 15 But the talk about him became widely. Crowds came to hear him and he healed many sick people. \v 16 But Yesu often moved out lonely places to talk with God.
\s1 Yesu healed a paralyzed man
\p
\v 17 One day while Yesu was teaching, Farasi men and teaching men of the law, who had come from other towns of Galili region, from Judia and from Jerusalem staying. The power of the Lord was there to heal the sick. \v 18 Some men carried a paralyzed man with a mat and tried to put him into the house to lay him before Yesu. \v 19 But they didn't find any way because of the crowd, so they took him up on the roof, and they opened the roof and put him down with rope through the small hole into the middle of people in fornt of Yesu.
\p
\v 20 When Yesu saw their big mind(faith), he said, "Friend, your sin are washed."
\p
\v 21 Farasi men and the teaching men of the law discussed with themselves, "Who is this man who speak bad/wrong talk(blasphemy)? Who can wash sins but God alone?"
\p
\v 22 Yesu knew what they were thinking and asked them, "Why are you thinking [these things] in your heart? \v 23 Which is easier to say; 'Your sins are wiped/washed,' o to say, 'Get up and go'? \v 24 But you may know that the Son of Man has authority on this world to forget sins." He said to the paralyzed man, "I tell you, get up, take your mat and go to the house." \v 25 Immediately he stood up in front of them, picked up what he had been lying and went back to the house praising God. \v 26 Everyone was amazed and praised God. They are full of the fear to God and said, "We have seen amazing things today!"
\s1 Yesu called Lefi
\p
\v 27 After this, Yesu went and saw a tax collector name Lefi sitting at tax collecting place(booth). Yesu told him, "Follow me." \v 28 And Lefi stood up, left everything and followed him.
\p
\v 29 From there Lefi made a big feast for Yesu at his house, and a large crowd of tax collectors and other people were eating with them. \v 30 But the Farasi men and the teaching men of the law complanied to his following men, "Why do you eat and drink with tax collectors and people doing sins (sinners)?"
\p
\v 31 Yesu answered them, "The healthy people don't look for a doctor but only the sick people [do]. \v 32 I didn't come to call straight people, but sinful people [come to call] to turn away.
\s1 People asked Yesu About fasting
\p
\v 33 They said to him, "Jon's following men often fast and talk with God, and also do the following men of Farasi men, but yours are in only eating and drinking." \v 34 Yesu answered, "Can you make the bridegroom's guest fast while he is with them? \v 35 But the day comes here when the bridegroom will leave from them, in those days they will fast."
\p
\v 36 Yesu told them this parable, "No one will tear from [a bit ] new clothes and put on the old clothes. If he does, he will tear new clothes, and he will not put with old clothes. \v 37 And no one will fill new alcohol into old alcohol container. If he does, the new alcohol will spoil alcohol container, the alcohol will run out and the alcohol container will be spoiled. \v 38 No, new alcohol must fill into new alcohol container. \v 39 And no one wants the new after drinking old alcohol, because he says that, "[The] old is well."
\c 6
\s Lord of the Sabbath
\p
\v 1 One Safat Yesu was walking through the grainfields, and his following men began to pick some head of grain, rubbed them in their hands to eat the seeds(kernels) \v 2 Some of Farasi men asked, "Why are you breaking the law on the Safat?
\p
\v 3 Yesu answered them, "Have you read what Deifid did when he and his groups were hungry? \v 4 He entered the house of God, and picked up blessed bread, he ate them which law is only burning sacrifice men to eat. And he also gave some to his friends." \v 5 Yesu said to them, "The Son of Man is Lord of the Safat."
\p
\v 6 On another Safat he went into the meeting house and began to teach, and a man was there whose right hand was paralytic. \v 7 Farasi men and the teaching men of the law were looking for reason to accuse Yesu, so they watched him to see if he might do healing work on Safat. \v 8 But Yesu knew what they were thinking and said to the paralyzed man, "Get up and stand in fornt of all people." So he got up and stood there.
\p
\v 9 Then Yesu said to them, "I ask you, which is lawful on the Safat: to do good or to do evil, to save life or to destroy it?"
\p
\v 10 He looked at them all, and said to the man, "Stetch out your hand." Paralyzed man did that, and his hand became good. \v 11 But they were angry and began to discuss with each other what they might do to Yesu.
\s The Twelve men with Yesu's authority
\p
\v 12 One day Yesu went to the sid of a monutain to talk with God, and talked with God to God all night to dawn. \v 13 When morning came, he called his following men and chose only 12, [whom] he gave the name people with Yesu's authority(men with Yesu's authority(apostles)), \v 14 Saimon whom he name Fitè, his young brother Endru, Jems, Jon, Filif, Batolome, \v 15 Metyu, Tomas, Jems son of Alfes, Saimon who wanted to save Ju people with power against Roman, \v 16 Judas son of Jems, Judas Iskariot who became a man who give teeth(betrayer).
\s Blessings and Woes
\p
\v 17 He went down with them and stood on level place. Many Yesu's following men was there and many [people] came from Judia, same way from Jerusalem, and from the coast of Taire and Sidon, \v 18 who had come to hear him and to be healed from their diseases. Who spoiled by evil spirit became good, \v 19 and all the people tried to touch him, because power was [coming] from Yesu and healing them.
\p
\v 20 He looked his following men and said,
\q1 Blessed are you who are poor,
\q2 because yours is the ruling of God.
\q1 \v 21 Blessed are you who are hunger now,
\q2 because you will be satisfied.
\q1 Blessed are you who weep now,
\q2 because you will laugh.
\q1 \v 22 Blessed are you when people see you with hate,
\q1 when people exclude you and insult you,
\q2 and reject you and said that you are evil spirit,
\q2 because of the Son of Man.
\p
\v 23 "Rejoice in that day and dance for joy, because your pay/reward is big in heaven. In a same way their ancesters treated God's people who make know(prophets)."
\q1 \v 24 "But How painful to you who are rich,
\q2 because you aready have easy life.
\q1 \v 25 How painful to you who are satisfied now,
\q2 because you will be hungry.
\q1 How painful to you who laugh now,
\q2 because you will be in sadness and in crying.
\q1 \v 26 How painful to you when all people speak good talk about you,
\q2 in a same way their ancesters treated and said to the false God's people who make know(prophets).
\s1 Love for Enemies
\p
\v 27 But I tell you who hear me: Love your enemies, do good to those who see you with hate. \v 28 Bless them who curse you, talk with God for those who mistreat you. \v 29 If someone strikes you on the cheek, turn to him to other side also. If someone takes your long coat, do not stop him from taking your other shirt. \v 30 Give to all people who asks you, if anyone takes what belongs to you, don't take it back. \v 31 Do to other people what you want them to do for you.
\p
\v 32 If you love those who love you, why should you receive a blessing? Like that sinners love those who love them. \v 33 And if you do good to those who are good to you, why should you receive a blessing? Like that sinners do that. \v 34 And if you lend [money] to those from whom you will pay back, why should you receive a blesssing? Like that sinners lend [money] expecting to pay back. \v 35 But love your enemies, do good to them, don't expect to get pay back. Then your pay/reward is big, and you will be sons of the Most High God, because he is kind to them who don't reply with thanking talk and sinners. \v 36 And be merciful, just as your Father is merciful.
\s To judge other people
\p
\v 37 Do not count people's sin because God will not count your sin. Do not say they are sinner to people, and them he will not say you are sinner. Forgive, and yours [sins] will also be washed. \v 38 Give to other people in order that God will give you again. If you do these things, you will see many, and he will give you until filled and poured your hand. How many do you give them, in a same way he will give it to you.
\p
\v 39 Yesu told them this parable, "Can a blind man lead a blind man? Will they not [both] fall down a hole? \v 40 The followers will be not above their teaching man, but if who have learned everything, he will be same to his teaching man.
\p
\v 41 Why do you look at dust in you friend's eye and do not see the log in your eye? \v 42 How [do] you say to your friend, 'Friend, let me take your dust in your eye,' when you don't see your log in your eye? You liar, first take out the log from your eye, and then you will see clearly to remove the dust from your friend's eye.
\s A Tree and Its Fruit
\p
\v 43 No good tree bears bad fruit, nor does a bad tree bear good fruit. \v 44 Every tree will bear their fruit. People do not pick mango from breadfruit tree o coconut from sego tree. \v 45 The good man produces good things(life) from good heart, and like this, the evil man produces bad things(sins) from evil heart. He speaks what [is] full in the heart.
\s Two house builder
\p
\v 46 Why do you call me, 'Lord, Lord,' and do not do like what I say? \v 47 I will put in clear place(show) how he is like who comes to me and listens my talks and put them in an action. \v 48 He is like a house builder, who dug down deep and built it on rock. When a flood came, it struck that house, but could not shake it, because it was built strong. \v 49 But [the one] who hears my talks and does not put them in an action, this man is like who buid a house in the muddy place. When flood struck that house, fell down completely."
\c 7
\s The big mind(faith) of the head man of Rom soldiers
\p
\v 1 When Yesu finished talk to the people, he went to Kafenamèn. \v 2 The worker of the head man of Rom soldiers(centurion), who he(his owner) pleased him very high, this man was sick and was close to die. \v 3 The soldiers' head man heard about Yesu, he sent Ju head men [to him], they asked Yesu to go and heal the sick. \v 4 When they came to Yesu, then they asked him, "This man told him to go and heal him, \v 5 because he loves our nation and built a meeting house for us." \v 6 So Yesu went with them.
\p
He was not far from the house that time the soldiers' head man sent friends to him to say, "Lord, don't trouble yourself. I can't ask you come to my house because I am sinner. \v 7 In this reason I am not worthy to come to you. But you will just say and then my worker will be good. \v 8 I myself am a man under authority, [and there] are soldiers under me. I tell this, 'Go,' and he goes, 'Come,' and he comes. I say to my worker, 'Do this,' and he does it."
\p
\v 9 When Yesu heard amazing talk from him, and he turned to the crowd following him, he said, "I tell you, I have not found such a big mind(faith) in Israil. \v 10 When the men [who were sent] returned to the house and found the worker well.
\s Yesu raised a widow's son
\p
\v 11 The other day Yesu went with his following men and a crowd to a town called Nain. \v 12 As he was about to arrive at the gate of the town, they saw [people] carrying out dead body of a widow's only son, and the crowd from the town was with her. \v 13 When the Lord saw her, he is full of mercy for the mother and he said, "Don't cry."
\p
\v 14 He moved close and touch the carrier, those who carried it stood. He said "Young man, I say to you, get upǃ" \v 15 The dead son got up [and] sat down and started to talk. Yesu gave him to his mother.
\p
\v 16 They were surprised and after they were happy and said, "A big God's man who make know(prophet) has arrived to us. God has arrived here to help his people. \v 17 This talk about Yesu became wide out to Judia and which close regions.
\p
\s Yesu and Jon the Baptist
\p
\v 18 Jon's following men told him about these things. Jon called two, \v 19 he sent two people to the Lord to ask, "Are you the one who is to come, or will(should) we wait for other people?"
\p
\v 20 When two men came to Yesu, they said, "Jon the baptist sent us to ask to you, "Are you the one who comes, or we will wait for other people?"
\p
\v 21 One good day Yesu healed many people who had different diseases and people with evil spirit, and make be people to see who were blind. \v 22 So he answered to the messengers, "Go back and say to Jon what you saw and heard. The blind became man [who] can see, the lame become walker, the leprosy are healed, the deaf become people [who can] hear, the dead are rasied, and the good talk is preached to the poor. \v 23 Blessed is the anyone who do not stop believing in me."
\p
\v 24 After this Jon's messengers.d left, Yesu began to talk to the people about Jon, "What did you go out into the desert to see? Are these long grass blowed by the wind? \v 25 If not, what did you go out to see? A man dressed in good clothes? No, those who wear good clothes and who had expensive things are in king's places(palaces). \v 26 But what did you go out to see? Prophet? Yes, I tell you, he surpassed all other God's man who make know(prophet). \v 27 This is the oneabout whom [it is] written,
\q1 'I will send the messenger ahead of [you],
\q2 who will prepare your way.'
\p
\v 28 Yeus said more, "I tell you, Jon the Baptist surpasses all men who have been born on this earth. But the one who is like a small child inside the ruling of God, he surpasses Jon."
\p
\v 29 When they heard Yesu's talks, all the people including to tax collects knew that God's way is true, because Jon baptized them. \v 30 But Farasi men and teaching men of the law rejected God's wanting for themselves, because they refused [that] Jon baptize them.
\p
\v 31 To what, I (can) hard to find/compare about these people? What are they like? \v 32 They are like children sitting in the exchanging place(market place) and calling out to each other,
\q1 "We played flute for you
\q2 and you did not dance!
\q1 We sang a funeral song,
\q2 and you did not cry!"
\p
\v 33 Jon the baptist came, he didn't eat food and didn't drink alcohol, and you say, 'He is with evil spirit.' \v 34 The Son of Man came, eating and drinking, and you say, "Here is a glutton and a alcohol drinker, a friend of tax collectors and sinners." \v 35 Wisdom is proved straight by her following men.
\s Yesu Anointed by a Sinful Woman
\p
\v 36 One of Farasi men invited Yesu for dinner, he went to Farasi man's house and sit to eat. \v 37 A woman had lived a sinful life in that town learned that Yesu was eating at one Farasi man's house, that woman brought a jar of the good smelling liquid(perfume), \v 38 woman stood behind him to [wash] his feet and knelt down to him, and wet Yesu's feet with her tears. She began to wipe them(2 feet) with her hair, and kissed them and poured special smelling liquid on them.
\p
\v 39 When this Farasi man who invited him saw this, he said to himself, "If this man is God's man who make know(prophet), he would know who is touching him and what kind of woman she is, she is a woman with sin."
\p
\v 40 Yesu answered him, "Saimon, I will say one talk [to you]."
\p
He said, "Tell me, teaching man."
\p
\v 41 Two men owed money to a moneylender, 5000 kina to one and the other 500 kina. \v 42 Both of them became no money to pay him back, so he forgave debt for both. Do you see who will very liking him?"
\p
\v 43 Saimon answered, "I think that who had deleted big payment back."
\p
Yesu said, "You answered well."
\p
\v 44 "Then he turned toward the woman and said to Saimon, 'Did you see this woman? When I came to your house, you did not give me any water for washing my feet, but the woman wet me with tears and wiped them with her hair. \v 45 You did not kiss me, but only this woman, from the timeI entered, has not stopped kissing my feet. \v 46 You did not put oil on my head for welcoming me, but she has poured special smelling liquid on my feet. \v 47 Therefore I tell you, this woman's many sins have been washed, because she has shown big love. But one who has been washed little loves little same way.
\p
\v 48 Then Yesu said to her, "Your sins have been washed."
\p
\v 49 The other guests began to say among themselves, "Who is this who washes sins?"
\p
\v 50 Yesu said to the woman, "Your big mind(faith) has saved you, go well and live."
\c 8
\s1 The Parable of the farmer
\p
\v 1 After this, Yesu traveled from one town and village to another, [he] preached the good talk about the ruling of God. The 12 were with him, \v 2 some women who had been healed from evil spirits and diseases, Meri Magdalin from whom 7 evil spirits have come out. \v 3 Erod's household mananger Kusa, his wife Joana, Susana and many other women. These women helped them with their things.
\p
\v 4 While a large crowd was gathering to Yesu from different towns, he preached parable:
\p
\v 5 "A farmer went out to sow his seed. When he scattered the seed, some fell along the road, it was trampled on, and the birds ate it. \v 6 Some seed fell on the land with stones, when it came up, it died because there is no water(moisture). \v 7 Other seed fell among the thorns place which it grew up with thorns and choked it. \v 8 Other seed fell on good land. It grew and produced a crop 100 times more than was sorn. When he talked this, he said, "He who has ears to hear, he will hear."
\p
\v 9 His following men asked him what is meaning of this parable. \v 10 He said, "God is showing to you what he did not show before about ruling of God, but I am speaking to other people with parables, so that,
\q1 The eye will see, but they may not find,
\q1 they will hear, but they may not understand.
\p
\v 11 The meaning of parable is this: The seed is the talk of God. \v 12 Those along the road are ones who hear, and then devil comes and steals [the talk] from their hearts, so that they may not truly approve(believe) and not be saved. \v 13 Those on the land with stone are ones who receive the talk with joy when they hear it, but they have no root. Their big mind(faith) is not long, but in the time of testing they fall away. \v 14 Which seeds fell among the thorns place, they stand for those who hear, but they expect/think/worry about many things to become rich in their life and their big mind(faith) do not grow strong. \v 15 But which seeds on good land stands for those with a good and true heart, who hear the talk, they endure and put it practice and produce other seeds."
\s Parable of a light
\p
\v 16 "People don't put lamp in the pot or put under the basket. But he will put on the table. \v 17 What is hidden will be found, and what is secret will be put out the sight. \v 18 Pay attention to how you listen. Whoever have something will be given more, but whoever does not have, and they think that mine are enough will lose."
\s Yesu' mother and his younger brothers
\p
\v 19 Yesu's his mother and his younger brothers came to see him, but because there are many people, they can't come to close to him. \v 20 Someone told him, "Your mother and your younger brothers are standing outside, waiting to see you."
\p
\v 21 He answered, "My mother and younger brothers are those who hear God's talk and put it action."
\s Yesu calms big wind(storm)
\p
\v 22 One day Yesu said to his following men, "Let's go to theh lake and pass over to the other side." So they got into the bout and went. \v 23 As they started, Yesu fell asleep. Big wind blew in the lake, so bout almost was sink, they were in the big problem.
\p
\v 24 The following men went and woke him, shouted, "Lord, Lord, we're going to drown!"
\p
He woke up and rebuked the wind and waves. Immediately big wind stopped [and] all became calm. \v 25 He said to his following men, "Where is your big mind(faith)?"
\p
The following men came to fear and amazement, they said themselves, "Who is he? When he speak to wind and waves, [they] obey him!"
\s Yesu healed man with evil spirit
\p
\v 26 They arrived at the region of Gerasenes, which is across from the Galili region. \v 27 When Yesu stepped out, a man with evil spirit met him. For the long time this man had not worn clothes and didn't stay in the house, but in the grave place. \v 28 When he saw Yesu, he shouted and fell at his feet, shouted loudly, "What do you want with me, Yesu, Son of the Most High God? I beg you, don't curse me!" \v 29 For Yesu said evil spirit to go out of the man. Many times evil spirits attacked him and people bound with chains on his hand and legs and was under the guard, [but]he broke the chain and evil spirit drove him into the clear places.
\p
\v 30 Yesu asked him, "Who(What) is your name?"
\p
He answered, "Many" because many evil spirits had come into him. \v 31 And they begged him repeatedly not to order that, 'We will not go to into the never ending hold.'
\p
\v 32 A large herd of pigs was feeding on the mountainside. Evil spirits begged Yesu to let them go into them, and he gave them power(permission). \v 33 When evil spirits came out of the man, they went to the pigs, and they rushed down steep bank to the lake and was drowned.
\p
\v 34 When the men looking for the pigs saw what had happened, they ran off and told this in the town and contryside. \v 35 And they came to see what had happened. When they came to Yesu, they found the man from whom evil spirits had gone out, staying at Yesu's feet. And he dressed and was with the straight mind. But they were afraid. \v 36 Those who had seen it told to the people how evil spirit possessed man had been became good(healed). \v 37 All the people from the Gerasanes begged Yesu to leave them, because they were full of fear. So they got into the bout to leave.
\p
\v 38 That man from whom the evil spirits gone out, he begged Yesu to go with him, but Yesu sent him with talk that, \v 39 "Return to the village and tell how much God has done for you." So the man went away and told through the city how much Yesu had done for him.
\s A dead girl and a sick woman
\p
\v 40 When Yesu went back, a crowd welcomed, because they were waiting for him with expecting. \v 41 The man name Jairus, a meeting house head man came and fell at Yesu's feet, begged him to go to his house \v 42 because his only daughter, [a girl] 12 years old was dying.
\p
When Yesu was on the way, the crowds packed tightly around him. \v 43 And a woman was there who had been bleeding for 12 years, but no one heal her. \v 44 She came him from backside and touched the edge of Yesu's clothes that time her bleeding stopped. \v 45 Yesu asked, "Who touched me?"
\p
When they all denied it, Fitè said, "Lord, the crowd are surrounding and pressing you."
\p
\v 46 But Yesu said, "Someone has touched me. I know [my]power has gone out from me."
\p
\v 47 When the woman came without watching man and without notice, she had a fear and knelt down at his feet. In front of all the people, she told why she had touched him and how she had been healed at once. \v 48 Then Yesu said to her, "Daughter, your big mind(faith) has healed you. Go in peace."
\p
\v 49 While Yesu was still speaking, someone came from house of Jairus, who was meeting house head man. He said, "Your daughter has died. Don't bother the teaching man anymore." \v 50 When Yesu heard this, he said to Jairus, "Don't be afraid. Believe and she will be good." \v 51 When he arrived at the Jairus' house, he didn't permit anyone to go with him except Fitè, Jon and Jems and her father and her mother. \v 52 While all the people were crying and shouted with sadness for her(moured for her). Yesu said, "Don't cry, she is not dead but asleep." \v 53 They laughed at him because she was dead. \v 54 But he took her by the hand and said, "My child, get up!" \v 55 Her spirit returned, immediately she stood up. Then Yesu told them to give the food. \v 56 Her parents were surprised, but he ordered them not to report [anyone] what had happened.
\c 9
\s Yesu sent out 12 following men
\p
\v 1 One day Yesu called his 12 following men together and he gave them power and authority to cast out evil spirits and to heal diseases. \v 2 And he sent them to preach about ruling of God and to heal the sick. \v 3 He told them, "Don't take anything in journey- no staff, no bag, no food, no money, no extra clothes. \v 4 Which house you enter, stay in there until you leave that town. \v 5 If people do not welcome you, shake the dust from your feet, must leave their town, [as] a it will be warning to them as God's punishement comes because they rejected his talk. \v 6 So they left and went from the village to the village, proclaiming God's good talk and healing people in every places.
\p
\v 7 Erod the ruler heard [about] all what was happening. And he worried because some were saying, 'This is Jon who had been raised from the dead,' \v 8 other people thought, 'Elaija appeared,' and other people thought that one of the God's people who make know(prophets) of long ago had come back to life. \v 9 But Erod said, "I had Jon's head cut off. Who is this I hear many talks about him?" And he wanted to see Yesu.
\s Yesu fed 5,000 people
\p
\v 10 When the men with Yesu's authority(apostles) returned, they told to Yesu what they had done. He took them and they went to rest to the town called Betsaida. \v 11 But many people knew about it and followed him. He welcomed them and spoke to them about the ruling of God and healed them who needed healing.
\p
\v 12 Late in the afternoon 12 following men came to him and said, "Send the crowd, they will go back to the close village and countryside in order to find food and sleeping place, because we came in remote place here.
\p
\v 13 He answered to them, "You(plural) give them something to eat."
\p
They answered, "We have 5 bread loaves and two fish, if we want to feed these people, we will [have to] go and buy their food." \v 14 There were about(?) 5,000 men. But he said to his following men, "Have them sit down groups make about(?) 50 each." \v 15 So following men did, and all the people sat down. \v 16 Yesu took 5 breads and two fish, and looked up the heaven, gave thanks and broke them. Then he handed them to the following men to give to the people.
\p
\v 17 All the people ate [and] were satisfied, and the following men picked up 12 basketfuls of broken pieces which were left over.
\s Fitè said clearly that Yesu is the Keriso
\p
\v 18 One day Yesu left the crowd for talking with God alone and his diciples were with him, he asked them, "Who do people say I am?"
\p
\v 19 They answered, "Some say Jon the baptist, other people say Elaija, but other people say one of God's man who make know(prophet) of long ago has come back to life."
\p
\v 20 He asked them, "But what about you? Who do you say I am?"
\p
Fitè answered, "God's Keriso."
\s Yesu spoke about his death
\p
\v 21 Yesu strictly warned them not to tell about this to anyone. \v 22 And he said, "The Son of Man must suffer many things and the head people, the leading sacrifice burning people(high priests) and the teaching men of the law rejected him, and they surely kill and after the three day he will rise to life."
\p
\v 23 Then he said to them all: "Whoever start to follow me, they must deny themselves and take their cross every day and follow me. \v 24 Whoever wants to save his life will lose it, but whoever loses his life because of me will save it. \v 25 And how good is it someone to gain the whole world, but lose or destroy themselves? \v 26 Whoever is with shame about me and my talk, the Son of Man will be with shame of him when he comes back in his strong light(big light) and in the big light(glory) of his Father and of the without.dust(holy) men carrying heavenly message(angels). \v 27 I tell you the truth, some who are standing here, they will see the ruling of God before they will die."
\s Three following men saw Yesu's big light(glory)
\p
\v 28 8 days later Yesu took Fitè, Jon and Jems with him [and] went [up] on a mountain to talk with God. \v 29 While he was talking with God, his face changed [its appearance], and his clothes became like as bright as lightening. \v 30 Two men, Moses a Elaija, appeared with big light(glory), [and they] talked with Yesu. \v 31 They spoke about his journey, which he would fulfill God's wanting by dying in Jerusalem. \v 32 Fitè and his group were very sleepy, but when they woke up, they saw his big light(glory) and two men standing with him. \v 33 As Moses and Eliaja were about to leave Yesu, Fitè said to him, "Lord, it looks good we are here with you. We will make three house, one for you, one for Moses and for Elaija." He didn't know what he said.
\p
\v 34 While he was speaking, a cloud appeared and covered them, and they were afraid when they entered the cloud. \v 35 A voice came from the cloud, said, "This is my son, whom I have chosen, listen to him." \v 36 When talk finished, they saw Yesu alone. They did not tell anyone at that time what they saw.
\s Yesu Healed a child with evil spirit
\p
\v 37 The next day, when they came back from the mountain, a large crowd met him. \v 38 A man cried out from the crowd, "Teacher, I beg you to look at my son, because he is my only child. \v 39 The evil spirit attacked him with a sudden shout, he throws him make strict and make him to foam at the mouth. The evil spirit does not leave and kept on destroying him. \v 40 I begged your following men to drive it out, but they are impossible [to do]."
\p
\v 41 Yesu answered, "You without big mind(faith) and without hearing people, how long must I stay with you and endure you? Bring your son here."
\p
\v 42 While the child was coming, the evil spirit threw him to the ground twisting. But Yesu rebuked the evil spirit, healed the child and gave him back to his father. \v 43 And they were amazed at God's big things doing.
\s Yesu spoke about his death a second time
\p
While all the people were amazed and they said Yesu's action doing, he said to his following men, \v 44 "Listen carefully to what I am about to tell you. The Son of Man is going to be gave teeth(betrayed) into the hands of men." \v 45 But they did not understand what is meaning. Because it was secret to them, they did not know it, and they were afraid to ask him about it.
\s Who will be big
\p
\v 46 His following men were arguing who will be big. \v 47 But Yesu knew their thoughts, so he had a little child stand there beside him. \v 48 Then he said to them, "Whoever welcomes this little child in my name welcomes me, and whoever welcomes me welcomes the one who sent me. Who is little among all of you, he is big."
\p
\v 49 Jon said, "Lord, we saw the man driving out evil spirits in your name and we tried to stop him, because he is not one of us."
\p
\v 50 Yesu said, "Don't stop him because whoever is not against us, he is for us."
\s Samaria people rejected Yesu
\p
\v 51 Yesu's day became close to go back to the heaven, Yesu strongly decided to travel to Jerusalem. \v 52 He sent messengers on ahead, who went to a Samaria village to prepare things for him, \v 53 but the people there did not welcome him, because he was going to Jerusalem. \v 54 When the following men Jems and Jon saw this, they asked, "Lord, do you want us to shout to the heaven fire down to destroy them?" \v 55 But Yesu turned and rebuked them. \v 56 And they went to another village.
\s Real following men/followers of Yesu
\p
\v 57 As they were walking along the road, a man said to Yesu, "I will follow you wherever you go."
\p
\v 58 Yesu answered, "Wild dogs have holes and birds have nests, but the Son of Man has no place to sleep and to rest."
\p
\v 59 He said to another man, "Follow me."
\p
But man answered, "Lord, first I will go back to home. After my father dies I will bury him, after I will foloow you."
\p
\v 60 Yesu said to him, "Those who are spiritually dead will bury the dead, but you go and proclaim talk of the ruling of God."
\p
\v 61 Another still said, "I will follow you, Lord, but first let me go back to my family to say goodbye."
\p
\v 62 Yesu answered, "Anyone who starts to work to plow and looks back, he is not able to work for the ruling of God."
\c 10
\s Yesu sent out 72 following men
\p
\v 1 After this the Lord chose 72 other following men and sent them two by two to every town and place where he wanted to go. \v 2 He told them, "Harvest season original food are ready to Dig are many but workers are few. Therefore ask the Lord of the harvest in the harvesting season, to send out workers into the origin food field. \v 3 Go! I am sending you out like helpless baby sheeps(lambs) among wild dogs. \v 4 Do not take money bag and traveling bag. Do not take other sandols, do not [spend] long [time] to greet with people on the road.
\p
\v 5 When you enter a house first say, 'Blessed to this house.' \v 6 If this blessing is [with] man there, your blessing will rest on him, if not, it will return to you. \v 7 Stay that house, eating and drinking whatever they give you, because workers should take their pay. Do not move around from house to house.
\p
\v 8 When you enter a town and are welcomed, eat what is ready to you. \v 9 Heal the sick who are there and tell them that, 'The ruling of God is near to you.' \v 10 But when you enter a town and they don't welcome you(are not welcomed), go into the road and say, \v 11 'We wipe the dust of your town [that] stick to our fee, we give warning to you. But remember about this: The ruling of God has been near.' \v 12 I tell you, it comes little on the judging day for Sodom, but there will be very high judgement in that town.
\p
\v 13 How bad will be to you, Korasin! How bad will be to you, Betsaida! For if the special workings(miracles) were did to you had been did in Taire and Sidon, they would have turn away long ago, sitting with sackcloth and ashes. \v 14 On the judgement day Taire and Sidon, their punishment will be very big, but your.p punishment will surpass their punishment. \v 15 And you, Kapenam, will you lift to the heaven? No, you will go down to never ending hole(hell).
\p
\v 16 Yesu said to his following men, "Whoever listens to you, he listens to me, but whoever rejects you, he rejects me, but whoever rejects me, he rejects him who sent me."
\p
\v 17 72 following men returned with joy and they told, "Lord, even evil spirits obeyed us in your name."
\p
\v 18 Yesu answered, "I saw Sáifèr fall like lightening from heaven. \v 19 Listen, I gave you authority to step on snakes and scopions and to overcome the power of the enemy, anything will not hurt you. \v 20 But do not rejoice because evil spirit submit you, but it is joy for you because your name are written in heaven."
\p
\v 21 At that day the God Spirit filled with joy to Yesu and he(Yesu) said, "I praise you, Father, Lord of heaven and earth, because you have hidden these things from the wise and intelligent, but revealed them to without-knowledge/intelligent men like children. Yes, Father, this was with your good blessing.
\p
\v 22 My Father has given me all things. No one knows the Son only the Father [knows], and no one knows who the Father is only Son [knows] and those to whom the Son chooses to reveal him."
\p
\v 23 Then Yesu turned to his following men and said privately, "Blessed are them who see what you see. \v 24 For I tell you that many God's people who make know(prophets) and ruling men(kings) wanted to see what you see, but they didn't see, and to hear what you hear but didn't hear it."
\s The parable of the good Samari man
\p
\v 25 One day a teaching man of the law stood up to test Yesu and asked, "Teacher, what I must to do to receive the eternal life?"
\p
\v 26 Yesu answered, "What is written in the law? How do you interpret it?"
\p
\v 27 He answered, "'Love the Lord your God with all your heart, with all your spirit, with all your power and with all your mind' and 'Love your neighbor like as yourself how do you love.'"
\p
\v 28 Yesu answered, "Correct, do this and you will live."
\p
\v 29 But he wanted to justify himself, so he asked Yesu, "And who is my neighbor?"
\p
\v 30 Yesu answered, "A man went to from Jerusalem to Jeriko, on the road robbers attacked him. They stripped him of clothes, beat him and leave him almost died and went away, \v 31 A burning sacrifice men was going that road but when he saw the man, he passed by through the other side. \v 32 Like this a man belong to Lefi family came and saw him, passed by the outside. \v 33 But Samari man was going like as, when he saw half dead [man] and he felt pity for him. \v 34 He went to him, painted on olive oil and alcohol, bandaged wounds. Then he put him on his donkey and brought him to an inn and looked after him. \v 35 The next day he gave two silver coins them to the house manager. He said, 'Look after him, when I return, if you use many money, I will pay you.
\p
\v 36 Which of these three do you think become a neighbor to the man who was striked by robbers?
\p
\v 37 The teaching man of the law answered, "The man who had mercy to him."
\p
Yesu told him, "Go and do like this."
\s Mata and Meri
\p
\v 38 Yesu and his following men were on the way, they arrived to the village, woman name Mata welcomed Yesu to her house. \v 39 Mata's small sister name Meri who sat the Lord's feet listening to what he said. \v 40 But Mata worried about her many works. So Mata came to Yesu and asked, "Lord, you know Meri has left me to do the work by myself? Tell her to help me!" \v 41 The Lord answered, "Mata, Mata, you are worried and made a trouble to mind about many things, \v 42 but one thing is necessary. Meri has chosen what is good, and it will not be taken way from her."
\c 11
\s Talking with God(Prayer)
\p
\v 1 One day Yesu was talking with God in a different/certain place. When he finished, one of his following men said to him, "Lord, teach us to talk with God, just as Jon taught his following men." \v 2 Yesu said to them, "When you talk with God, say like:
\q1 Father,
\q2 Be honored your without.dust(holy) name,
\q2 your kingdom will come.
\q1 \v 3 Will give us food in every day.
\q1 \v 4 Forget us our sins,
\q2 because we forget their sins those who did against us.
\q1 And do not bring us in temptation."
\p
\v 5 Then Yesu said to them, "If one [of you] have a friend, and you should go to him at midnight and say, 'Friend, give me three loaves of flawè, \v 6 because my friend has come to me from long distance, and I have no [food] to prepare for him!'
\p
\v 7 Who was inside answered, 'Don't bother me. The door is already locked, my children and I went to sleep. I can't get up and give you.' \v 8 I tell you, if he will not get up and give a bread because you are his friend, but he will get up and give you all what you need, you are not shame because you continue to ask him.
\p
\v 9 So I say to you: Ask and it will be given to you; seek and you will find; knock and the door wll be opened to you. \v 10 Because every people who ask will receive, every people seek will find; the one who knocks, the door will be opened.
\p
\v 11 You father, if your child asks for fish, will you give him a snake, is it possible? \v 12 Or if he asked an egg, what will you give him a scorpion? \v 13 So even though you are evil, you know [how]to give good things to your child. How much more good will your Father in heaven give the God Spirit to those who beg him!"
\s Yesu a Beljebab
\p
\v 14 One day Yesu drove out a evil spirit from mute man, and when evil spirit left, the man who was mute began to speak. The crowd was surprised. \v 15 But some of them said, "By name of Beljebab, the head man of evil spirit, Yesu is driving our evil spirits." \v 16 Others tested Yesu [and] they asked asking talk doing somethings from heaven.
\p
\v 17 Yesu knew their thoughts, so he said to them: "Which country began to divide against itself will ruined, and which house began to divide against itself will fall down. \v 18 If Sáifér began to divide himself, how will his country stand? I say this because you think that I might cast out evil spirit by name of Beljebab. \v 19 If I cast out evil spirit by the name of Beljebab, by whose name your followers drive them? Your followers prove [that] you are not straight. \v 20 But if I cast out evil spirit by the power of God Spirit, then the ruling of God is here to you.
\p
\v 21 When a strong man arms himself and guards his home when everything he owns are safe. \v 22 But if very strong man strikes and defeats him, he carries away the fight things which the owner was depending on and divides up what he stole.
\p
\v 23 Who is not with me, he is man rejecting me, and who does not gather with me, he is scattering.
\p
\v 24 When evil spirit comes out from a man, it goes clear place to search for rest. But when it does not find, will say, 'I will go back to the house I lived.' \v 25 When it returns and finds house is swept clear and good prepared. \v 26 Then evil spirit goes and brings other 7 spirits more wicked than itself, they enter and live there. And man's life became more worse than before how he was.
\p
\v 27 When Yesu was saying these things, a woman called out [to him] in the crowd, "Blessed is the woman who gave birth to you and [let you] nurs at her breasts!"
\p
\v 28 Yesu answered, "Blessed are those who hear God's talk and put it in practice."
\s The surprising thing of Jona
\p
\v 29 When the crowds became many, Yesu said, "These are very wicked crowd. They are asking God's surprising thing, but I will not give anything [but] only the surprising thing of Jona. \v 30 As Jona was a surprising thing to Ninèfa people, like as the Son of Man will be a surprising thing to this people group. \v 31 The queen of the Sifa country will stand at the judgement this people group and will condemn them that they are sinner; because this woman came to Solomon from the long country. And one man are here big, over Solomon. \v 32 Ninèfa people will stand at the judgement to this people group and will condemn them because they turn away at Jona's preaching. And one man are here big over Jona.
\s The lamp of the body
\p
\v 33 No one lights will not put where will be hidden, or under the big basket. But he put it on its stand, so that when [people] who come, they can see the light. \v 34 Your eyes are a light for your body. If your eyes are good, your whole body will be in the light. But when your eyes are bad, your body will be in the darkness. \v 35 Be careful that the light in you should not darkness. \v 36 So if your body is in the light, any part of body will not be in the darkness, it will be full of light as when light of lamp shines to you.
\s Yesu said strong talk Farasi men and teaching men of the law
\p
\v 37 When Yesu had finished speaking, a Farasi man invited him to eat with him. \v 38 But Farasi man came to surprise because Yesu began to eat without washing hands.
\p
\v 39 The Lord said to Farasi man, "You Farasi man clean the outside of the cup and pot, but inside of you are [full of] greed and wickedness. \v 40 You foolish men! [Didn't] you know the one who made the outside, also made inside? \v 41 But give away what is inside you to the poor, everything will be clean for you.
\p
\v 42 Woe/how terrible to you Farasi men, because your offering is to God from all the garden, but you neglect God's love and justice. You should have practiced the love of God and justice, and don't stop offering of garden food.
\p
\v 43 Woe to you Farasi men, because you like to find the good(important) seat in meeting house, and respectful greeting in the marketplaces.
\p
\v 44 Woe/how terrible to you Farasi men, because you are like unmarked graves, which people walk on without knowing it.
\p
\v 45 One of the teaching man of law answered, "Teacher, when you say these things, you spoil/attack us also."
\p
\v 46 Yesu answered, "You, the teaching men of the law, woe to you, because you put people down with burdons they are heavy to carry, but you will not lift on finger to help them.
\p
\v 47 Woe/how terrible to you, because you build the graves for the God's people who make know(prophets), whom your ancesters had killed. \v 48 You testify that it appove what your ancesters did; they killed God's people who make know(prophets) and you built their graves. \v 49 In this reason, God with his wisdom said, "I will send them God's people who make know(prophets) and men with Yesu's authority(apostles), but they will kill some and will also chase other people. \v 50 So the people of this time will be responsible because God's people who make know(prophets)' blood bleeding from the beginning, \v 51 from blood of Abel to the blood of Jakaraya, who was killed between the table for burning sacrifice and without.dust(holy) place. Yes, I tell you, the people of this time will be held responsible for it all.
\p
\v 52 Woe/how terrible to you the teaching man of the law, because you have kept the key to open the door of knowledge. You yourselves have not entered inside, and you have stopped those who were entering.
\p
\v 53 When Yesu left there, Farasi men and the teaching men of law became angry and they made a asking talk about many things, \v 54 they waited, [they] will catch Yesu through what he will say wrong talk.
\c 12
\s Warning and encouragement
\p
\v 1 When crowd had gathered, so they were stepping on each other. Yesu began to talk first his following men [and] said, "You must guard yourself from Farasi men's lying life. \v 2 The day is coming everything what is covered will be discovered, and what is hidden will be revealed. \v 3 What you have said in the dark will reveal to the light, and what you have whispered into the ear will be proclaimed to the roofs of house.
\p
\v 4 I tell you, my friends, don't be afraid those who kill the body and after this they cannot do anything. \v 5 But I show you who you should look with fear: look God with fear, after killing you, he has authority who throw you into fire(hell). Yes, he is truly the one who you should see with fear. \v 6 Are it 5 small birds sold for 20 toya? But one of them is not forgotten in God. \v 7 Yes, your hairs are counted by God. Don't be afraid. You.p surpass small birds.
\p
\v 8 I tell you, anyone who declare publicly that they belong to me, the same way the Son of Man will declare they belong to me before the men carrying heavenly message(angels) of God. \v 9 But anyone who denies me before people I will also deny them before the men carrying heavenly message(angels) of God. \v 10 Anyone who speaks against the Son of Man can be washed, but anyone who speaks bad talk(blasphemes) to the God Spirit will not be washed.
\p
\v 11 When you are brought to meeting houses, to rulers and authorities, do not worried about how will you defend yourself or what you will say, \v 12 because God Spirit will teach you at that time what will say."
\s The parable of rich fool
\p
\v 13 Someone in the crowd said to him, "Teacher, tell my big brother to divide what my father's left things."
\p
\v 14 Yesu answered, "Friend, who appointed me in order that I divide things between two men?" \v 15 Then he said to them, "Be careful! Because of your every kind of greed; because possessions/things do not save your life.
\p
\v 16 Then Yesu told them this parable: There was a rich man who was land owner what produce good crops. \v 17 He thought, 'What shall I do? My place is no enough where I will store all my things.' \v 18 Then he said, "This is what I will do. I will tear down my crops storage house and build very big, and there I will store my farm crops and other things. \v 19 And I will say in my mind, "There are many good things to me to keep many years. Take life easy; in eating food and drink alcohol and be happy."
\p
\v 20 But God said to him, 'You fool! This night your life will be demanded from you. So who will take everything what you have prepared for yourself?
\p
\v 21 This is how will be anyone who stores things for himself but is not rch in God."
\s Don't worry
\p
\v 22 Then Yesu said to his following men, "Therefore I tell you, don't worry because of your life, what you will eat; because of your body and what you will wear. \v 23 Food and clothing are important but behavior is very important. \v 24 Look at the crows: they do not plant and dig, there is no their storage house; but God feeds them. You are of high regard in God's eyes and surpass those birds! \v 25 Can you live how long by worrying about it? \v 26 If you cannot this small things, why do you worry about other things?
\p
\v 27 Look how wild flowers grow. They do not make their clothes. But I tell you, even Solomon in all his beautiful things [that] he dressed are not good but flower are good. \v 28 If God clothes the grass of the bush, which are here today and tomorrow are thrown into the fire. How much more he will clothe you? What little big mind(faith) you have! \v 29 You do not downheart about food and water, do not worry about it. \v 30 Because outsiders of the world carry having this things, and your Father knows what you need. \v 31 But seek the kingdom of God, and these things will be given to you enough.
\p
\v 32 Don't be afraid, little group, because your Father is in pleasure to give you the ruling of God. \v 33 Sell your what you have and give to the poor. Provide money bag for yourselves which it will not be finished, your treasure will be in heaven where will be not finished away, because there is no thief can come and no moth can destroy. \v 34 Because where your treasure is, your heart will be there.
\s Be Watchedness
\p
\v 35 Be always ready for God's work all the days and nights, \v 36 like workers waiting for that his master will return from wedding feast, when he returns and knocks they can immediately open the door for him. \v 37 How happy will be those workers their master finds they are ready when he comes back. I tell you the truth, he will take off wedding clothe to serve workers, [and] he will tell to sit food table and will give them food. \v 38 How happy will be those workers their master finds them ready, when he returns this day in the middle of the night or at daybreak. \v 39 But you must know: If owner of house had known at which hour the thief will come, he would not let the thief to break his house. \v 40 You must be ready, because the Son of Man will come at this hour when you do not expect him without ready.
\p
\v 41 Fitè asked, "Lord, are you speaking this parable only for us or every people?"
\p
\v 42 The Lord answered, "Who is with big mind(faith) and good manager? He is the one his master will put to manage the house to give them food at [proper] time? \v 43 How good is to this worker when his master finds him doing his work when he returns. \v 44 I tell you truly, he will put him to manage all his things. \v 45 But worker might say to himself, 'My master take a long day to come,' and he begins to beat working men and women, and eats food and drinks alcohols to get drunk. \v 46 The master of that worker will return on that day when he does not know. His master will punish him by death and he will put him with the people who do not truly approve.
\p
\v 47 The worker who knows the master's desire but does not ready or does not do his master's desire, he will be beaten a lot. \v 48 But worker who does not know and he does badly, he will be beaten few. From every people who has been given many, same big will be demanded. And from who has been entrusted a lot, same big will be given.
\s Not peace but division
\p
\v 49 "I came to bring fire on the earth, I think fire were already burning but it does not burn! \v 50 Firstly I must suffer bigly, how terrible am I until my suffering will be finished! \v 51 Do you think I come [to] bring peace on the earth? No, not peace but division. \v 52 From now one family of 5 will be divided, three against two and two against three. \v 53 They will be divided, father against son and son against father, mother against daughter and daughter against mother, mother-in -law against daughter-in-law and daughter-in-law against mother-in-law."
\s Understanding the time
\p
\v 54 He said to the crowd, "When you see a black cloud rising from west, really you say, 'It's going to rain,' and it rains. \v 55 And the south wind blows, you say, 'It's going to hot,' and it happen. \v 56 Liar! You know how to interpret the surprising thing of the earth and sky. You don't know how to interpret the present days.
\p
\v 57 "You yourself know what is straight. \v 58 If anyone find your guilty, settle the case before you go to the court. If not, he may drag you court. So judging man will hand you to the police and the police throw you into darkness house, \v 59 I say, you will not get out until you have paid all the money."
\c 13
\s Turn away or die
\p
\v 1 At that day some people were there who told Yesu about the Galili region people whose blood Failet mixed with their sacrifices. \v 2 Yesu answered, "How do you think those Galillans' sin which they did surpass the sins that other men from Galili region did, that's why they saw pains this way? \v 3 I tell you, no! But If you don't turn away to God, all of you will die. \v 4 Or those 18 who die when tower of Siloam fell to them, what do you think their sin surpass of the other men who were in Jerusalem? \v 5 I tell you, No! But if you don't turn away to God, all of you will die way."
\p
\v 6 Then he told this parable, "A man have a fruit tree growing in his garden, and went to take fruit, but he find none. \v 7 So he said the man who looked after the garden, 'For three years now I have been coming to take fruit on the fruit tree, but I haven't found any. Cut it down! Why should it grow and eat the land? \v 8 The man answered, 'Lord, Leave it alone for one more year, and I will dig around it and fertilize it. \v 9 If it bears fruit next year, good! If not, cut it down.'"
\s Crippled woman was healed on the Safat
\p
\v 10 One Safat Yesu was teaching in one of meeting houses, \v 11 and a woman was there who had been crippled by evil spirit for 18 years. She was bent over and can't straighten up. \v 12 When Yesu saw her, he called her and said, "Woman, you are good." \v 13 Then Yesu put his hands on her, and immediately she straighten up and praised God!
\p
\v 14 The meeting house head man was angry because Yesu healed her on the Safat, he said to the people, "There are 6 days for working. So come to heal on those days, not on the Safat."
\p
\v 15 The Lord answered him, "You liar! You always untie cow and donkey from the stall and lead it out to give it water on the Safat. \v 16 Then this woman, a daughter of Ebraam, whom Sáifèr has kept to bound for 18 years. She should be saved on the Safat from what bound her."
\p
\v 17 When Yesu said this, his enemies was full of shame, but the people rejoiced what Yesu did good.
\s Parables of the small seed and the Yeast
\p
\v 18 Then Yesu asked, "How is like the ruling of God? What shall I compare it to? \v 19 [It is] like small seed, a man took and planted in his garden and grew and became a tree, and the birds make nest in this branches."
\p
\v 20 Again Yesu asked, "What shall I compare the ruling of God to? \v 21 It is like yeast a woman took and mixed into 3 bags of flour. So all the flour rises [and] become big dough."
\s The narrow door
\p
\v 22 When Yesu went to Jerusalem, he taught them through the town and village. \v 23 Someone asked Yesu, "Lord, are only a few people possible to be saved?"
\p
He said to them, \v 24 "Work hard in order that you will enter small door, because I tell you, many people will try to enter and will not happen. \v 25 When house owner will get up and will close the door, you will stand outside, knocked and said, "Lord, open the door for us.'
\p
But he will answer, 'I don't know you or where you come from?
\p
\v 26 Then you will say, 'We ate and drank with you, and you taught us on the roads.'
\p
\v 27 Then he will answer, 'I don't know you or where you come from. Get away from me, all of you evil doing people!
\p
\v 28 There will be weeping and gnashing of teeth, when you see Ebraam, Aisak and Jeikof and all the God's people who make know(prophets) in the ruling of God, but you are thrown. \v 29 People will come from east and west and north and south, and will take their places there at the feast in the ruling of God. \v 30 Who are last they will be first, who are first they will be last.
\s Yesu' sorry for Jerusalem
\p
\v 31 At that time some Farasi men came to Yesu and said to him, "Leave this place and go the other place. Erod wants to kill you."
\p
\v 32 He answered, "Go tell that small wild dog(fox), 'I will cast out evil spirit, and heal people today and tomorrow, and on the third day I will finish my work.' \v 33 But I must keep on going today and tomorrow and next day, any God's man who make know(prophet) cannot die outside of Jerusalem!
\p
\v 34 "O Jerusalem, Jerusalem, you who kill the God's people who make know(prophets) and strike whom sent to them by stone, I wanted to gather your people, like as hen gather her chicks under her wings, but you did not want it! \v 35 Look, your city will be left. I tell you, you will not see me again until you say, 'Blessed is the one who comes in the name of the Lord!"
\c 14
\s Yesu at a Parasi men's house
\p
\v 1 One Safat, when Yesu went to eat in the house of respected Farasi men, the people were watching him very close. \v 2 There was a man whose arms and legs were swollen came to Yesu. \v 3 Yesu asked Farasi men and the teaching men of the law, "What is lawful to heal on the Safat or not?" \v 4 But they remained silent. Yesu took man and healed him and sent him.
\p
\v 5 Yesu asked them, "If one of you has child or cow fallen into a well on the Safat, will you not rush to get it out? \v 6 And they didn't say any talk.
\p
\v 7 When he noticed the guests chose the good place at the table, he told them this parable: \v 8 "When someone invites you to a wedding feast, don't take a high place. May it not be that that place is already reserved for a man that he has invited who has a high reputation & surpasses you.s \v 9 If he did, one who invited you will come and say to you, 'Give this person your place.' How he is shameful, you should take last place. \v 10 But when you are invited, take low place, [so that]when your host comes, he will say to you, 'Friend, move up to high place.' You will be honored in front of the guests. \v 11 Those who make themselves big will come down low, those who come down themselves will go up high."
\p
\v 12 Then Yesu said to his host, "When you give a lunch or dinner, you don't invite your friends and brothers and relatives or the rich friends, if you do, you will be invited and will be repaid. \v 13 But when you give a food [banquet], invite the poor, the crippled, the lame, [and] the blind. \v 14 They cannot repay you. But God will bless you and repay when his people rise from death.
\s Parable about big feast
\p
\v 15 After Yesu finished teaching, one of guests said, "Blessed is the one who will eat at the feast in the ruling of God!"
\p
\v 16 Yesu answered, "A man prepared a big feast and invited many guests. \v 17 On the feast day, he sent his workers to tell those who had been invited, "Come, everything is now ready.'
\p
\v 18 But they began to make excusing talk. The first man said, 'I have bought a field, and I will go to see it. Excuse me.'"
\p
\v 19 Another said, "I have bought 5 cows, and I'm on the way to try them out. Excuse me.'
\p
\v 20 Still another said, 'I just got married, so I can't come.'
\p
\v 21 The workers returned and told to his master. Then house's owner became angry and ordered his workers, 'Go out quickly small roads and ouside/bush roads in the town and bring the poor, the crippled, the blind, and the lame.'
\p
\v 22 The worker said, 'Lord, what you said has been done, but there are still place(room).'
\p
\v 23 Then the master told his workers, 'Go out to small roads and bush roads and demand strong them 'Come in,' so that my house will be full. \v 24 I tell you, those who were invited first will not get taste of my food(banquet)'"
\s Being a following man
\p
\v 25 A large crowd went with Yesu, and he turned them and said to them. \v 26 "If anyone comes to me to be my following man, he should love me a lot, secondly he should love father and mother, wife and children, brothers and sisters, yes, even his life. If not, he cannot be my following man. \v 27 And if anyone who don't carry his cross and follow me and he can't be my following man.
\p
\v 28 "If the man who wants to build a big house, he will sit first and estimate and see how much money to finish it. \v 29 He will start to build the house, but he cannot finish. So every people [who]see what he does will make fun of him. \v 30 They will say, "This man began to build but could not finish."
\p
\v 31 What king will do if he has 10,000 soldiers could defend himself against a king who is about to attack him with 20,000 soldiers? Before he goes out to battle, he should first sit down and decide if he can win? \v 32 If he is not able to, he send messanger while other is still a long way and he will asked terms of peace. \v 33 Like this way, you leave everything, you will be my following man.
\p
\v 34 Salt is good, but if its flavor is finished, how can it be made to taste salty again? \v 35 It is not good for the soil or for anything, [so]people throw it out.
\p
Whoever has ears, he must hear this talk."
\c 15
\s The lost sheep
\p
\v 1 The tax collectos and sinners were all gathering to hear him. \v 2 But Farasi men and teaching men of the law began to gramble, "This man welcomes sinner to eat with them."
\p
\v 3 Then Yesu told them this prarble, \v 4 "If one man has 100 sheep and loses one, what does he do? He surely leave 99 in open place and go to find lost sheep until he finds. \v 5 When he finds it, he is happy, [and] put it on his shoulder. \v 6 He will go the house. Then he called his friends and his neighbors and told them, "Rejoice with me. I have found my lost sheep." \v 7 I say to you.p, in heaven the same kind of big happiness will happen when a sinner turns away. Truly the rejoicing about 99 straight men who have no sin, it is very little, but the rejoicing about one sinner who turns away will be very big.
\s The lost coin
\p
\v 8 "What will a woman do if she has ten silver coins and loses one. She surely lights a lamp and begens to sweep the house [and] looks carefully until she finds it. \v 9 Then when she find it, she calls friends and neighbors and told to them, "Make a feast with me, I have found my lost coin." \v 10 I said to you in the same way there is rejoicing in the front of the men carrying heavenly message(angels) of God when one sinner who turns away
\s The lost son
\p
\v 11 Yesu began to say again, "There was a man with two sons. \v 12 The younger son said to his father, 'Father, I will not wait until you die. Now give me your things what will belong to me.' Then he divided things(property)between his two sons.
\p
\v 13 So not a long later, the younger took his [things] what had, packed up and went to long country and began to waste money in bad living. \v 14 After this when ran out everything, there was famine in the land, so he began to feel starving. \v 15 So he went to work and asked to a man in that land, and the man sent him to feed pigs. \v 16 He was very hungry, he want to eat pigs' food. But no one who gave him anything.
\p
\v 17 When he came back to thought, he said, 'All of my father's workers have enough food, and here I am dying! \v 18 I will go back to my father and say, "Father, I had sinned to the heaven and you. \v 19 I am not enough to be called your son; treat me like your worker. \v 20 So he stood up and went to his father.
\p
But while he was still a long way, his father saw him and full of mercy for him; he ran to his son and hugged him and kissed him.
\p
\v 21 The son said to his father, 'Father, I had sinned to the heaven and you. So I can't be called your son.' \v 22 But his father said to his workers, 'Hurry! Bring new clothes and put it on him. Get a ring for his finger and sandols on his feet. \v 23 Bring the fattened cow and kill it. Let's make feast and rejoice, \v 24 for this son of mine who was dead and now he is alive; He was lost and now he has been found.' So they rejoiced.
\p
\v 25 At that time, the first son was in the field. When he came close the house, he heard singing sound and dancing. \v 26 So he called one of the workers and asked him what was happening. \v 27 He answered, 'Your small brother has arrived, and your father has killed fattened cow because he is here and is good.' \v 28 So first born son became angry and would't go into the house. His father came out and begged him to enter. \v 29 But he answered his father, 'Look! All years I have worked for you and have never disobeyed your talk. But you didn't give us to young goat in order that we will do feast with friends. \v 30 But when this your son who wasted your money in bad living [and] come back to the house, you killed the fattened cow for him!
\p
\v 31 His father said, "My son, you are always with me. Everything I have is yours. \v 32 But we celebrate and rejoice because your younger brother was dead and now is alive. He was lost and now is here."
\c 16
\s The clever manager
\p
\v 1 Yesu told his following men, "A rich man chose a man to look after his things. But the rich man was told that his manager had wasted your money. \v 2 So he called him and asked him, "What is this I heard about you? Give me knowledge(report) about your work how did you look after, because you cannot be manager after this."
\p
\v 3 The manager said to himself, 'What shall I do now? My master is taking away my work. I'm not strong to dig, and I am shame to beg. \v 4 I know what shall I do so that people will continue to welcome me into their houses when I lost my work'
\p
\v 5 So he called one by one his master's people to pay back. He asked the first man, 'How much pay do you put my master's? \v 6 He answered, '20 drums of olive oil.' Manager told him, 'Take your paper, sit down quickly, and write 10 drums.'
\p
\v 7 He asked again the second man, 'How much is to you? He answered, '1,000 flawè bags .' He told him, 'Take your paper. Write 800 flawè bags.'
\p
\v 8 The master praised his dishonest manager because he deal with well. The people of this world deal well but the people of the light are not like them. \v 9 I tell you, become friend for yourself with worldly things. When it is gone, you will be welcomed into an eternal village.
\p
\v 10 Whoever is faithful in small things, he is also [faithful]in large things. Whoever lies in little things, he is also[lying] in large things. \v 11 So if you are not true(faithful) to manage worldy things, how will be true(faithful) with true riches? \v 12 And you are not true to manage someone's things, who will give you your own things?
\p
\v 13 A worker cannot stay under two owners ruling. He will hate the one and love the other. You will obey to the one and deny the other. Therefore you cannot stay under two ruling, God and money.'
\p
\v 14 The Farasi men are money lovers. When they heard this talk and made fun of Yesu. \v 15 Yesu said to them, "You are ones who make yourselves look good in the eyes of people, but God knows your heart. What is value highly to people's thought is without.meaning to God's sight.
\p
\v 16 Moses' law and God's people who make know(prophets)' teaching were proclaimed until Jon's day. From that time, the good talk about the ruling of God started to preach, every people is trying to get in to the ruling of God. \v 17 Heaven and earth will disapper, but little talk in God's talk will not remove.
\p
\v 18 Anyone who divorces his wife and marries another man commits adultery and man who marries a divorced woman commits adultery.
\s The rich and Lajarus
\p
\v 19 There was a rich man who wore very good clothes and lived in good every day. \v 20 At the gate of his house there was a beggar name Lajarus who was with sores, \v 21 and wanted to eat what fell from the rich man's table. At that times the dogs came and licked his sores.
\p
\v 22 The begger died and men carrying heavenly message(angels) took him there to Ebraam. So the rich man died and was buried. \v 23 In the without-sun hole(hell), the rich was suffering, when he looked up and saw Ebraam far off, with Lajarus by his side. \v 24 So he cried out, 'Father Ebraam, have pity on me and send Lajarus to dip his hand in water and become cool my tongue, because I am suffering in this fire.'
\p
\v 25 But Ebraam answered, 'Son, remember there your living days(lifetime), you lived in good [things], while Lajarus had nothing, but now he is resting here and you are suffering. \v 26 Another reason, it is impossible because big hole seperate between us, anyone who want to cross from here to you are difficult.'
\p
\v 27 He answered, 'Then I beg you, father, send Lajarus there to my father's house, \v 28 because I have 5 small brothers. Let them know they will not come to this suffering place.'
\p
\v 29 Ebraam answered, 'There are books Moses and the God's people who make know(prophets) wrote, they should listen/obey to them.'
\p
\v 30 He said, 'No, father Ebraam, if the dead returns to them, they will turn away.'
\p
\v 31 He said to him, 'If they do not listen/obey to Moses and the God's people who make know(prophets), they will not turn away also same way if someone returns from the dead to life.'"
\c 17
\s Teaching about forgetting(washedess) and Faith
\p
\v 1 Yesu said to his following men, "Which things always cause people to sin, but[how] painful to this person whom people cause. \v 2 To tie the person a big stone around neck and throw into the sea, even this would be a small heavy for you.s. But Who cause this children to sin, your.s heavy would be big. \v 3 So watch yourselves.
\p
"If your big brother do sins, correct him, and if he turn away, wash him. \v 4 If he do sins against you 7 times in a day and 7 times come back again to you and saying, 'I had turn away,' you wash them."
\p
\v 5 The men with Yesu's authority(apostles) said to the Lord, "Lord, add our big mind(faith)!"
\p
\v 6 Yesu answered, "If your big mind(faith) is like a small seed, you can say to this big tree, 'be uprootes and planted in the sea,' and it will obey you.
\p
\v 7 If your worker comes back from plowing or from looking after the sheep. Will master say, 'Come [and] sit down to eat.'? \v 8 But he will say, 'Cook my food, and get ready and wait on me while I eat. After that you may eat.' \v 9 Will he give thank his worker because of his work what he was told to do? \v 10 It is same with you, when you have done everything what you were told to do, say, 'We are only your workers. We have only done our work."
\s 10 men with leprosy
\p
\v 11 Yesu were walking to Jerusalem, traveled between Samaria and Galili region. \v 12 When he entered a village, 10 lepers met him. They stood at a distance, \v 13 and shouted loudly, "Yesu, Yure, have mercy on us!"
\p
\v 14 Yesu saw them and said, "Go, show yourselves to the burning sacrifice man." And while they went, they were made clean.
\p
\v 15 One [of them], when he saw he was healed, came back, praising God loudly. \v 16 He knelt down at Yesu's feet, gave thank him and he was man from Samaria.
\p
\v 17 Yesu asked, "What were cleased all of ten? Where is other 9 men? \v 18 Why only this foreigner came back to praise God?" \v 19 Then Yesu said to him, "Stand and go. Your big mind(faith) has made you heal." '
\s The ruling of God
\p
\v 20 One day Farasi men asked Yesu, "When the ruling of God would come?" Yesu answered, "The ruling of God does not come this way you see with your eyes. \v 21 You can't say, 'Here it is' or 'There it is' because the ruling of God is inside you.
\p
\v 22 Then Yesu said to his following men, "The day comes here when you will wish to see one of days of the Son of Man, but you will not see it. \v 23 People will tell you, 'There he is, or 'Here he is.' Don't follow after them. \v 24 Because when the Son of Man comes, all the people will see him like the lightening flashes [and] light up from one side to the other. \v 25 But first he will see/have many suffering and be denied by this generation.
\p
\v 26 Just as it was the days of Noa, it will same way in the days of the Son of Man. \v 27 People ate food and [drinking] water, men married to women up to the day Noa entered very boat. Then the flood came and destroyed them all.
\p
\v 28 It was the same in the days of Lot. People were eating food and [drinking] water, exchanging things, planting food and building house. \v 29 But in that day Lot left Sodom, fire and buring stone fell down from heaven like a rain, and destroyed them all.
\p
\v 30 It will like this on the day of the Son of Man is revealed. \v 31 On that day those who are outside of house must not go inside to get things. In the same way, who is in the field must not go back to take things. \v 32 Rembember Lot's wife! \v 33 Whoever try to keep his life will lose it, whoever loses his life will save it \v 34 I tell you, on that night two people will be sleep on the one sleeping place, God will take away one, [and] the other will be left. \v 35 Two women will prepare food together, he will take one and the other leave. \v 37 They asked, "Where, Lord?"
\p
Yesu answered, "Where is the dead body, there the eagles will gather."
\c 18
\s The parable of the widow and judging man
\p
\v 1 Yesu told his following men a parable to show them they should always talk with God and not to stop. \v 2 Yeus said, "In a town there was a decision maker(judge) who was without-fearing God and without-respecting people. \v 3 There was a widow in that town who continue to [come] always to him with talk, 'Give me justice in this arguing with enemy.'
\p
\v 4 The judge ignored her to some day, but finally he said to himself, 'I am without-fear to God and without-respect to men, \v 5 but this widow keeps on bothering me, I will see it that she gets her justice, so that she won't keep on coming to me!'
\p
\v 6 Then the Lord said, "Listen to what that unjust judge says. \v 7 God surely will bring about justice for his chosen men, who cry out to him day and night. He will not continually deny them. \v 8 I tell you, he will see that they receive justice quickly. But the Son of Man comes back, will he find anyone with big mind(faith) on earth?
\s Farasi men and tax collectors
\p
\v 9 Yesu told this parable to some one who look down as they think, 'I am straight man and he is not,' \v 10 "Two men went to the worshipping house to talk with God, one was Farasi man and the other is tax collecter. \v 11 Farasi man stood [and] talked with God, 'God, thank you that I am not like other men, robbers, sinners, adulterers, or like that tax collecter over there. \v 12 I fast two days a week, and I always give offering [that] Moses law require for God.
\p
\v 13 But the tax colletor stood a distance. He would not even look on to heaven, but beat his breast and said, 'God, mercy on me, I am a sinner.'
\p
\v 14 I tell you, this sinner, not Farasi man, he went back home with joy in front of God. If you exalt yourself to other people, you will be put down, and if you are down yourself, you will be ontop."
\s The children and Yesu
\p
\v 15 People brought children for Yesu to bless. When the following man saw this, they stop them. \v 16 But Yesu called children to himself and said, "Let children to come to me, don't stop children because the ruling of God is for the people like a children. \v 17 I tell you the truth, anyone who does not receive the ruling of God like a children cannot enter it."
\s The rich man
\p
\v 18 A Juwish head man asked him, "Good teaching man, what should I do to take the eternal life?"
\p
\v 19 Yesu answered, "Why do you call me good? Who is no good only God himself. (There no good except God alone.) \v 20 You know the commandments, 'No adultery, don't kill people, don't steal, don't lie, respect father and mother.'"
\p
\v 21 He said, "Since I was baby, I obeyed all these laws."
\p
\v 22 When Yesu heard this, he said to him, "You are still lack one thing to do. Sell all of yours and give them to the poor, and you will be rich man in heaven. Then come, follow me."
\p
\v 23 When he heard this talk, he saw with sadness because he was very rich man. \v 24 Yesu looked at him and said, "How hard it is for the rich to enter the ruling of God! \v 25 The difficulty of a camel to go through the needle's hole is big, but the difficulty of a rich man to enter the kingdom of God surpasses that thing."
\p
\v 26 Those who heard on this asking, "Who can be saved?"
\p
\v 27 Yesu answered, "What is hard to man is easy to God."
\p
\v 28 Fitè said to him, "We left all of what we have, [and] followed you!
\p
\v 29 Yesu said to them, "I tell you truly, I know every people who has left house, wife, big brothers, parents, children for the reason of the ruling of God \v 30 will see many times today in this life, and will see eternal life from God on next age(in the future)."
\s Yesu said again his death
\p
\v 31 Yesu took 12 following men aside, and told them, "We are going to Jerusalem, and everything is written this by God's people who make know(prophets) about the Son of Man will happen. \v 32 He will be handed over the outside men, and they will mock him, insult him, spit on him. \v 33 They will flog him and kill him. After three day he will rise again." \v 34 But following men didn't understand about this. Its meaning was hidden from them, and they did not know what he was talking about.
\s Yesu healed a blind beggar
\p
\v 35 As Yesu approched Jeriko, a blind man was sitting beside the road, begged. \v 36 When he heard the crowd passing by, he asked what was happening. \v 37 They told him, "Yesu of Najaret is passing by."
\p
\v 38 He cried out, "Yesu, Son of Deifid, have mercy on me!"
\p
\v 39 Those who was in the way rebuked him and told him, "Be quiet!" But he shouted with more big sound, "Son of Deifid, have mercy on me!"
\p
\v 40 Yesu stopped and ordered the man to bring him to him. When he came near, Yesu asked him, \v 41 "What do you want me to do for you?"
\p
He said, "Lord, I want to see!"
\p
\v 42 Yesu said to him, You will able to see! Your big mind(faith) saves you." \v 43 Immediately his eyes was opened and he followed Yesu, praised God. When all the people saw it, they praised God in a same way.
\c 19
\s Tax collecter Jekies
\p
\v 1 Yesu was going through Jeriko. \v 2 There was a man name Jekies, he was the chief tax collector who was rich. \v 3 He wanted to see Yesu, but he was a little man [so] he can't see him because he surrounded in crowd \v 4 So he ran ahead and climbed on a big tree like a wanj tree to see Yesu, while Yesu was coming that way.
\p
\v 5 When Yesu arrived at that palce, Yesu looked up him and said to him, "Jekiyes, come down quickly. I must stay at your house today." \v 6 So he came down quickly and welcomed him to his house with joy.
\p
\v 7 All the people saw this thing and began to grumble, "He went to become the guest to a sinner."
\p
\v 8 But Jekies stood and said to Lord, "Look, Lord! Now and here I divide half my things [to give] to the poor, and if I have cheated to the people anything, I will pay back 4 times their payment."
\p
\v 9 Yesu said to him, "Today salvation is into this house, because this man is Ebraam's descendant. \v 10 For the Son of Man came to look for and to save the lost."
\s The parable of ten workers
\p
\v 11 When they were listening to this, he preached the parable because he was close to Jerusalem and people thought that the ruling of God might appear suddenly. \v 12 He said, "A head man went away to a distant country so that he himself become a king and will come back again. \v 13 So he called ten workers and gave each of them same big amount money. He said, 'Fut this money to work until I come back.'
\p
\v 14 But his people saw him with hate and sent different woking group(delegation) after they said, 'We don't want this man will become our king.'
\p
\v 15 "He became a king so he return to village(kingdom). Then he sent for the workers to whom he had given the money in order to know how much money they made.
\p
\v 16 The first one came and said, "Lord, your money has earned ten times more.'
\p
\v 17 His owner answered, 'That's good, my good worker! Because you have become true(faithful) in a very small money work, you will take care of ten cities.'
\p
\v 18 The second came and said, 'Lord, your mina has earned 5 times more.'
\p
\v 19 His owner answered, 'You will take care of 5 cities.'
\p
\v 20 The third worker came and said, "Lord, here is your money. I kept your money and hid them with clothe. \v 21 I was afraid of you because you are a hard man. You take what did not put in and reap what you did not plant.'
\p
\v 22 His owner answered, 'I will judge you by your own talk, you are wicked worker! You knew that I am hard man and I take back what isn't mine and I harvest what I have not planted.' \v 23 Why didn't put my money in the place of producing money(bank) so that when I come back, I can collect it with interset?'
\p
\v 24 Then he said to those who were standing close, 'Take his money from him and give it to the one who has ten moneys.'
\p
\v 25 They said, 'Lord, his has already become ten moneys!'
\p
\v 26 He answered, 'I tell you that to every people who has many, will be given to them many, but those who has nothing, will be taken away. \v 27 But my enemies who without-want methat I will be their king, bring them and kill them in front of me.'
\s Yesu enter Jerusalem as a king
\p
\v 28 After Yesu said this he went in front of [them] to Jerusalem. \v 29 When he became close to Betefes and Betani on the mountain called Olif, he sent his two following men, said to them, \v 30 "Go into to the village first, when you enter it, you will find donkey tied, who didn't ride. Untie it and bring it here. \v 31 If anyone asks you, 'Why are you untying it?' say to him, 'The Lord needs it.'"
\p
\v 32 Those who were sent went and found it how he had told them. \v 33 As they untied donkey, that owners asked them, "Why are you untying donkey?"
\p
\v 34 They answered, "It is Lord' need."
\p
\v 35 They brought it to Yesu, threw their clothes on the donkey and Yesu got on that. \v 36 As Yesu went, people spread their clothes on the road.
\p
\v 37 When he came near and reached on that place where [road] sloped down to the Olive mountain, all of Yesu's following men began song/praise with joy to God in loud voices, reason because they had seen special workings(miracles) from Yesu:
\q1 \v 38 "Blessed are you the king who comes in the name of the Lord!
\q1 peace in heaven and big light(glory) in the very high(highest)!"
\p
\v 39 Some of the Farasi men in the crowd said to Yesu, "Teacher, rebuke your following men!"
\p
\v 40 He answered, "I tell you, if they keep silent, the stones will cry out."
\p
\v 41 When Yesu was arriving close to Jerusalem, he saw the city, Yesu began to weep about this [city] \v 42 and said, " Jerusalem people, I want you to know today what things bring peace to you, but you didn't know. Because it is hidden from your eyes. \v 43 The days will come to you when your enemies will surround you and block you from every side. \v 44 They will destroy you to the ground, you and your children in your place. They will not leave a stone on another, because you did not recognize God's salvation for you.
\s Yesu in the worshipping house
\p
\v 45 Then Yesu entered into the worshipping house courts and began to chase out [the people]who were exchanging things. \v 46 He said to them, "It is written in the God's talk, 'My house will be house of talking with God.' but you made it robber hidding hole.'
\p
\v 47 Everyday he was in teaching at the worshipping house. But the leading sacrifice burning people(high priests), the teaching men of the law and the head men wanted to kill Yesu. \v 48 But they couldn't find a way to kill him, because all the people's mind tied up his talk.
\c 20
\s The authority of Yesu questioned
\p
\v 1 One day when he was teaching the people in the worshipping house courts and preaching the good talk, the leading sacrifice burning people(high priests) and the teaching men of the law with head people, came to him. \v 2 They said, "Tell us by what authority you are doing these work. Who gave you this authority?"
\p
\v 3 He answered, "I will also ask you a asking talk(question). Tell me, \v 4 Jon's baptism comes from heaven or from human?"
\p
\v 5 They discussed it among themselves and said that, "If we say, 'From heaven,' he will ask, 'Why didn't you truly approve(believe) him?' \v 6 But if we say, 'From men,' all the people will stone us because they knew that Jon was a God's man who make know(prophet)."
\p
\v 7 So they answered, "We don't know where it come from."
\p
\v 8 Yesu said, "I will not tell you by what authority I am doing these work."
\s Parable about people looking after field(Tenants)
\p
\v 9 He went to tell the people this parable, "A man planted a vine tree in the field, left it to the workers and went away for a long time. \v 10 At harvesting time he sent a worker to people [who] look after the field(tenants) so that they will give him some fruit of vine tree from that field, but the tenants striked him and sent him back empty without things(empty-handed). \v 11 He sent second worker like that, but they also beated this man and treated with shame and sent him empty-handed. \v 12 He sent third man and they hit him with blood and threw him.
\p
\v 13 The owner of the grape fruit vine garden said, 'What shall I do? I will send my son whom I love. Surely they will respect him.'
\p
\v 14 But when the tenants saw him, they said to each other, 'This is the son of the owner of the grape fruit vine garden. Let's kill him, and farm things will be ours.' \v 15 So they threw him out of the grape fruit vine garden and killed him.
\p
"What will owner of the grape fruit vine garden do to them? \v 16 He will come and kill those men and give the grape fruit vine garden to other people."
\p
When the people heard about this, they said, "From here it won't be."
\p
\v 17 Yesu looked to them straightly and asked, "Then what is the meaning of that which is written,
\q1 'The post which the builders rejected and became the middle post.
\p
\v 18 Everyone who falls on the stone will be broken pieces, and when it falls on to them, they will be destroyed.'"
\p
\v 19 The teaching men of the law and the leading sacrifice burning people(high priests) looked for a way to arrest him quickly, because they knew that he spoke this parable about them. But they were afraid of the people.
\s Paying taxes to [Rom high ruling man] Kaisar
\p
\v 20 They watched him, and send checking man(spies) who pretend to be good. They tried to think to catch Yesu so that he will say diffent saying, so that they might hand him over to the governor. \v 21 The spies asked him, "Teacher, I know that you speak and teach what is straight and you are not influenced by people's thinking, but you teach the way of God truthfully. \v 22 Is it straight for us to put the money to [Rom high ruling man] Kaisar or not?"
\p
\v 23 Yesu saw their lying/trick and said to them, \v 24 "Show me his money. Whose face and name are these on it?"
\p
They reanswered, "[Rom high ruling man] Kaisar's"
\p
\v 25 Yesu said, "Give to [Rom high ruling man] Kaisar what is his, and give to God what is his."
\p
\v 26 They became without-way to catch Yesu saying anything wrong there in front of the people. They were amazed at his answer, and they became silent.
\s The rising and marriage
\p
\v 27 Some of Saduki men, who say that there is no rising, came to him. They came to ask Yesu. \v 28 They said, "Teacher, Moses wrote a law for us that if a small brother's big brother dies and leaves a wife but no children, his small brother must marry the widow and must produce children for his big brother.
\p
\v 29 There were 7 sons. The first one married and died childless. \v 30 The second married the widow, but he also died, leaving no children. \v 31 And the third married the widow, in the same way that 7 died, leaving no children. \v 32 Lost of them, the woman died. \v 33 At the resurection whose wife will she be? Because the 7 married her.
\p
\v 34 Yesu answered them, "Men will marry in this earth. \v 35 But in the future, those who can rise from death will not marry. \v 36 And they will not die. They will be like the men carrying heavenly message(angels). They will be God's children because God will rise them from death. \v 37 But when Moses wrote about burning bush fire, he showed that the dead will rise to life. He called the Lord 'The God of Ebraam, the God of Aisak and the God of Jeikof.' \v 38 He is not God of the dead, but God of the living, because they all are alive to him. \v 39 Some of the teaching men of the law responded, "Well said, teaching man!" \v 40 And no one[dared to] ask him any question talk.
\s Whose son is Keriso
\p
\v 41 Yesu asked them, "Why [do] people say that Keriso is the son of Deifid? \v 42 Deifid himself put in clear in the book of Psalms and said,
\q1 'The Lord said to my Lord:
\q2 Sit here at my right hand.
\q1 \v 43 until I put your enemies
\q2 under your feet.'
\m
\v 44 Deifid called him 'Lord.' How can he be his son?"
\p
\v 45 As all the people were listening, Yesu said to his following men, \v 46 "Protect yourselves from the teaching men of the law. They like to walk around with long clothes and to be respected in the markets, and their mind were sitting in the respecting places in the synangogues and they like to find the respecting places at feasts. \v 47 They take widows' things with cheating and they pretend to be good by making long talking with God in front of people(in public). These men will carry the pains most high.
\c 21
\s A widow's offering
\p
\v 1 As Yesu looked up, he saw rich people putting offering things in the worshipping house. \v 2 He saw a poor widow putting in two small coins. \v 3 He said, "Truly I tell you, this poor widow surpasses them who put the money. \v 4 All these people put the little things from many things, but widow put every thing for his living."
\s Signs of last days
\p
\v 5 Some of his following men were talking about how worshipping house decorated with good stone and offered things to dedicate God. but Yesu said, \v 6 "Everything what you see here, the day come where one stone will not leave from another people, everything will be thrown down to land."
\p
\v 7 They asked, "Teacher, when will these things happen? And what will be the surprising thing in order that this things are about to happen?"
\p
\v 8 He answered, "Be careful of deceiving. Be alert because many people will come in my name, with talk that, 'I am Yesu,' and 'The day is near.' Don't follow them. \v 9 When you hear of wars and surprising things, don't be afraid. These things will have to happen first, but land's end will not come yet.
\p
\v 10 Then he said to them, "One nation and other nation, they will fight, one kingdom and other kingdom, they will fight. \v 11 There will be big earthquakes, and famines, serious deseases in many places and fearful events and big surprising thing in heaven.
\p
\v 12 But they will hand you over and put you into suffering after [this] these things will happen. You will be tied in meeting houses and you will be put in darkness house, and you will be taken in front of ruling men(kings) and governers for my name. \v 13 But this will be time to tell about your big mind(faith). \v 14 But don't worry in the mind beforehand how will defend yourselves. \v 15 I will give you talk and wisdom in order that your enemies will not remove you or tell you are liar. \v 16 You will be gave teeth(betrayed) by fathers, mother people, brothrs, family, friends and they will put some [of you] to death. \v 17 Everyone will see you with hate because of me. \v 18 But your one hair of your head will not be lost. \v 19 You will stand firm in order that you will see real life. \v 20 When you see Jerusalem being surrounded by soldiers, you will know that its destruction is not.far. \v 21 Know [those] who are Judia people must go to the mountain, [those] who are in the city must go out, [those] who is outside of city must not enter the city. \v 22 Those day become with body(fulfilled) which it has been written about suffering. \v 23 How painful it will be pregnant women these day and nursing mother people! There will be big suffering in the land and anger to this people. \v 24 They will be cut by the bush knife to kill and other people will be taken as darkness house men(prisoners) to all the nations. Jerusalem will be trampled by Side people until outside man's day are finished. \v 25 There will be surprising things in the sun and moon and stars. On the earth, through all nations will be mental pain and in worring because wave roaring sound of the sea. \v 26 People fell down with fear, because pain what comes to the land, because the body of heaven will be shaken. \v 27 In that day they will see the Son of Man coming back in a cloud with power and big big light(glory). \v 28 When these things began to happen, stand up and lift up your head, because your salvation is near.
\p
\v 29 He told them this parable, "Look at the fig tree and all the trees. \v 30 When they begin to come up new leaves, you can see for yourselves and know that sunny season is near. \v 31 Like this, when you see these things happening, you will know that the ruling of God is near.
\p
\v 32 I tell you the truth, some of the people of this generation will still be arive when all the things happens. \v 33 Heaven and earth will pass away, but my talks will never pass away.
\p
\v 34 Be careful, don't let your hearts be dulled by drinking alcohol and singing feast and by world mind because this day will arrive suddenly like a trap. \v 35 Because this day will come on all those who live in this earth. \v 36 Always watch out and talk with God that you can be saved from what are happing, and you can stand firmly in frnt of the Son of Man."
\p
\v 37 Every day Yesu was in teaching at the worshipping house, and he spent every night on the mount of Olif. \v 38 All the people came early each morning to hear him at the worshipping house.
\c 22
\s Judas went to Betray Yesu
\p
\v 1 The festival of unleavened/without yeast flawè, called Passover became near. \v 2 The leading sacrifice burning people(high priests) and the teaching men of the law were looking for catching Yesu, because they were afraid of the people. \v 3 Then Sáifèr entered Judas Iskariot who was one of 12 following men. \v 4 And Judas went the leading sacrifice burning people(high priests) and worshipping house guarders and discussed with them how he might give teeth(betray) Yesu. \v 5 They were pleased and offered to pay him some money. \v 6 Judas went back and looked for the way to catch Yesu in place without-people.
\s The last feast
\p
\v 7 The day came for unleavened flawè which is Passover lamb being sacrifice. \v 8 Yesu sent Fitè and Jon and said, "Go to prepare for us to eat Passover food."
\p
\v 9 They asked, "Where do you want us to prepare for it?"
\p
\v 10 Yesu answered, "When you enter the city, you will see a man carrying a jar of water. You follow him the house that he enters, \v 11 and say to the owner of the house, 'Teacher asks, "Where is the guest room, where I may eat the Passover food with my following men?"' \v 12 He will show you a largh room upstairs, all furnished. Be ready(Prepare) there."
\p
\v 13 They left [and] found things like as Yesu how told them. So they prepared the Passover food.
\p
\v 14 When the time came, Yesu and his men with Yesu's authority(apostles) sit at the eating place. \v 15 And Yesu said them, "I wanted very much to eat the Passover food with you after [this] I will see the suffering. \v 16 I tell you, I will not eat again until this fulfill in the ruling of God.
\p
\v 17 After taking a cup, he gave thanks and said, "Take this and divide it among you. \v 18 I tell you I will not repeat [to drink] alcohol again until the ruling of God arrives."
\p
\v 19 He took flawè(bread), gave thanks and broke it, and gave it, with this talk, "This is my body which is given for you. Do this for remembering me."
\p
\v 20 In the same way, after the supper he took a cup, saying this, "This cup is the new without.lying talk(promise) in my blood which is poured out for you. \v 21 But the man who will be give teeth(betray) me is with me here. \v 22 The Son of Man will die on the God's want/will, but how terrible that man who betrays him!" \v 23 They began to ask among themselves who is here who would give teeth(betray).
\p
\v 24 Then they started to argue among them who will be big. \v 25 Yesu said to them, "The ruling men(kings) of Side people become owner with power to rule their people over, but they said, 'People's friend are.' \v 26 But you will not be like that. But who is big must be like a child, and who is head man must be like worker. \v 27 Who is big, the one who is at the table or the one who is worker? It is the one who is at the table. But I am among you who is worker. \v 28 You are those who have stood by me in my trials. \v 29 And I gave you the power for the ruling of God just as my Father gave me the power, \v 30 so that you will eat and drink in my table in the ruling of God, and will sit on high places, [and] will stand to judge 12 tribes of Israil.
\s Yesu say Fite's denial
\p
\v 31 Yesu said, "Saimon, Saimon, God gave authority for Sáifèr to test you as a farmer do to remove bad [seeds] from good seeds. \v 32 But I talked with God for you, Saimon, that your big mind(faith) may not fall. When you have turned back to me, you must strengten your younger brothers. "
\p
\v 33 But he answered, "Lord, I am ready to go with you to darkness house and to death."
\p
\v 34 Yesu answered, "I tell you, Fitè, you will deny me three times that you don't know about me after [this] the rooster crows today."
\p
\v 35 Then Yesu asked them, "When I sent you without money bag, without big(traveling) bag or without sandols, what did you miss?
\p
They answered, "No[thing]"
\p
\v 36 He told them, "But now if you have a money bag and small bag, take it, and if you don't have a knife, exchange clothes with a knife. \v 37 It is written by God's talk, 'And he was number(was counted) among the sinners.' I tell you that this things must happen to me. Yes, what is written about me must happen."
\p
\v 38 The following men said, "See, Lord, here are two knife."
\p
He answered, "That's enough."
\s Yesu talks with God on the mount of Olif
\p
\v 39 Yesu went out as usual to the mountain name Olif, and his following men also followed him. \v 40 When they reached that place, he said to them, "Talk with God that you will not fall into temptation." \v 41 He walked on a little bit from them and he knelt down and talked with God, \v 42 "Father, if your wanting is, take this suffering from me, not my wanting, but your wanting will happen."
\p
\v 43 An man carrying heavenly message appeared to him and helped him. \v 44 Yesu was in big pain, he talked with God with whole heart and his sweat fell down like drops of blood falling to the ground.
\p
\v 45 When he got up from talking with God and went back to his following men, he found them asleep, exausted because of sorrow. \v 46 Yesu asked them, "Why are you sleeping? Get up and talk with God so that you won't fall into temptation."
\s Yesu held
\p
\v 47 While Yesu was still in talk, a crowd came and the man who was called Judas one of 12 following men, he led them. He came up Yesu and kissed him. \v 48 But Yesu asked him, "Judas, are you betraying the Son of Man with a kiss?"
\p
\v 49 When Yesu's following men saw what was about to happen, they said, "Lord, should we cut them with our knifes?" \v 50 And one man cut the right ear of the worker of the leading burning sacrifice man.
\p
\v 51 But Yesu said, "Don't this!" And Yesu touched man's ear and healed him.
\p
\v 52 Then Yesu said to the leading sacrifice burning people(high priests), worshipping house guarders and the head people, who had come to him, "Am I head man of people without hearing(the rebbellion)? Why you come with knifes and clubs? \v 53 Every day I was with you in the worshipping house, you did not find with anger. But now your day have come, when the power of darkness is to you."
\s Fitè denied Yesu
\p
\v 54 They held Yesu, [and] brought to the house of the chief burning sacrifice men. Fitè followed at a distance. \v 55 And when they had kindled a fire in the middle of courtyard and they sat down together, Fitè also sat with them. \v 56 A working girl saw him seated in the firelight. The girl recognised him and said, "This man is one of Yesu's following man."
\p
\v 57 But he dinied it and said, "Woman, I don't know him."
\p
\v 58 Little later other man also saw him and said, "You are one of them."
\p
He answered, "Man, I'm not!"
\p
\v 59 About a hour later other man said strongly that, "He is Yesu's close man, who is from Galili region."
\p
\v 60 Fitè answered, "Man, I don't know what you're talking about!" As he was speaking, the rooster crowed. \v 61 The Lord turned and looked Fitè. Fitè remembered Lord's talk how he said to him, "You will denied me three times after [this] a rooster will crow today." \v 62 And he went out clear place and wept big tear.
\s Watching man make fun of Yesu
\p
\v 63 The man who were guarding Yesu made fun of him and beat him. \v 64 They blindfolded him and said, "Say! Who hit you?" \v 65 And they kept saying many bad talk to him.
\s Yesu are in fornt of Failet and Erod
\p
\v 66 At daybreak the head people of the people and the leading sacrifice burning people(high priests) and the teaching men of the law gathered and brought Yesu in front of them. \v 67 They said, "If you are Keriso, tell us."
\p
Yesu answered, "If I said you, you wouldn't truly approve(believe) me, \v 68 and if I asked you, you wouldn't answer to me. \v 69 But from now on, the Son of Man will be seat at the right side of the With Strong Power(Almighty) God."
\p
\v 70 They all asked, "Are you the son of God?"
\p
Yesu answered, "You say straight that I am." \v 71 Then they said, "What we will find other saying? We have heard it from him."
\c 23
\s Yesu stood before Failet
\p
\v 1 Everyone brought Yesu to Failet. \v 2 They began to accuse him with this talk, "This man tricked our people with this talk, 'Don't put money to Kaisar, Rom high ruling man and cliams with name to be Keriso, the ruling man(king).'"
\p
\v 3 So Failet asked Yesu, "Are you the ruling man(king) of Ju people?"
\p
Yesu answered, "Yes, you said that."
\p
\v 4 Failet said widely(announced) to the leading sacrifice burning people(high priests) and the crowd, "I don't find this man what is bad."
\p
\v 5 But they said strongly, "He is causing trouble through all Judia by his teaching, from Galili region to Jerusalem here!"
\p
\v 6 When Failet heard about this, he asked, "Is this man from Galili region?" \v 7 When he learned that Yesu was under the Erod's ruling, Failet sent him to Erod, who was in Jerusalem at that time.
\p
\v 8 When Erod saw Yesu, he was so pleased because for a long time he had been waiting to see him. From what Erod heard about him, he wanted to see other surprising thing. \v 9 Erod asked him a lot of questions, but Yesu did not answer to him. \v 10 The leading sacrifice burning people(high priests) and the teaching men of the law were standing there, they said with the angry(accused) him. \v 11 Then Erod and his soldiers made fun of him and insulted him. They dressed Yesu with the ruling man(king)'s clothes, they sent him back to Failet. \v 12 That day Erod and Failet became friends, before this they were been enemies.
\p
\v 13 Failet called together the leading sacrifice burning people(high priests) and head men and other people, \v 14 and said to them, "You brought Yesu to me who was a troublemaker. But I tried to ask him in front of you and I have not found him any sins which you say he has done. \v 15 Erod didn't find him guilty so he sent him back to us, 'He has not done anything to the death. 16-17\~
Therefore I will whip him after [this] let him go."
\p
\v 18 But they shouted with a one mind, "Kill him, take Baraba out to us!" \v 19 Barabas was thrown to darkness house because he was a head man of group in Jerusalem that fight against Roman Government and for murder. \v 20 Failet wanted to take Yesu out, so he spoke again to the crowds. \v 21 But they kept shouting, "Crucify him! Crucify him!"
\p
\v 22 For the third time he said, "Why? What sins has he done? I have not found him the reason to put him to death. I will beat him after [it] set him free."
\p
\v 23 But they shouted with loud, "Crucify him!" and with their loud shouts insisted that Yesu be put to death. \v 24 So Failet agreed to their wanting. \v 25 He released Barabas who had been thrown into darkness house for fighting with/against government and murder, permitted Yesu to their wanting.
\s Yesu is nailed to the cross
\p
\v 26 When the soldiers led Yesu away, there a man name Saimon from Sairene village, who was traveling to the other city, and put the cross of Yesu him on his shoulder to carry it behind Yesu.
\p
\v 27 A large people was following Yesu, women was there who are crying for him. \v 28 Yesu turned and said to them, "Women of Jerusalem, you do not cry for me! You cry for yourselves and for your children. \v 29 The day will come when you will say, 'Blessed are the childless women, the wombs that never bore and in the same way the breasts never nursed!" \v 30 They will say to the mountains, "Fall on us!" and to the small mountains(mountains), "Cover us!" \v 31 Because if people do these things when the tree is living, what will happen when it is dry?"
\p
\v 32 Two other men, were thiefs, also were led out to be put to death with Yesu. \v 33 When they came to the place called Golgota, which means "The skull," there they crucified Yesu with two thiefs, one on his right, the other on his left. \v 34 Yesu said, "Father, wash their sins, they do not know what they are doing." And they divided Yesu's clothes by throwing dice.
\p
\v 35 Many people stood watching this happening, the head men made fun of Yesu. They said, "He saved other people; let him save himself, if he is God's Keriso, his chosen son."
\p
\v 36 The soldiers made fun of Yesu. They brought him sour alcohol, \v 37 and said, "If you are the ruling man(king) of the Ju people, save yourself."
\p
\v 38 There were written notice above him, which said, "This is the ruling man(king) of the Ju people."
\p
\v 39 One of thiefs hunged beside of Yesu, said to Yesu, "Are you Keriso? Save yourself and save us!
\p
\v 40 But the other thief rebuked him and said, "You should fear God, [because] you are under the same sentence. \v 41 We are punished justly because of our sin we did. But this man didn't do anything wrong." \v 42 Then he said, "Yesu, remember me when you come into your ruling of God."
\p
\v 43 Yesu answered him, "Truly I tell you, today I will be with you in rejoicing country(pradise).
\s The death of Yesu
\p
\v 44 It was about noon, and darkness come over the land until it became middle of the afternoon, \v 45 because the sun stopped shinning. The thick cothes [curtain] of the worshipping house was torn in two from top to bottom. \v 46 Yesu shouted loudly, "Father, I put my spirit in your hands!" When he had said this talk, he died.
\p
\v 47 Roman soldier head man saw what happened, he praised God and said, "Surely this was a straight man." \v 48 When all the people who had gathered see what happened, they beat their breasts in sorrow and went away. \v 49 But all those who knew him and women had followed him from Galili region, stood at a distance and watched these things.
\s The burial of Yesu
\p
\v 50 There was a man name Josef, Juwish Ju head men's meeting's respected man(a member of the Ju head men's meeting) a good and straight man, \v 51 who he did not agree their thinking(opinion/decision). He came from the judia people's town, Aramatiat and he was waiting for the ruling of God revealing. \v 52 He went to Failet to ask Yesu's body \v 53 Then he took it down, wrapped in cloth in order that place it in a grave there no one had yet been entered. \v 54 This work did quickly in Friday because Safat was about to began.
\p
\v 55 This women who had come with Yesu from Galili region followed Josef and saw the grave and how his body was laid in it. \v 56 They went home to prepare good smelling liquid(perfumes). But they rested on the Safat like as Moses law.
\c 24
\s Resurrection
\p
\v 1 Sunday early morning, women carried special smelling liquids which they had prepared and went to grave. \v 2 They found the stone rolled away from grave enterance, \v 3 but when they entered, they did not find Lord Jesu's body. \v 4 While they were wondering where is Yesu's body, suddenly two men appeared in shining white clothes stood beside them. \v 5 In fear women bowed down to the ground, but these men said to them, "Why are you looking for who are living among the dead? \v 6 He is not here! He has risen! Remember how he told you, while he was with you in Galili region, \v 7 'The Son of Man will be handed over to the hand of sinners, be crucified and on the third day will be raised again.' \v 8 Then they remebered his talks.
\p
\v 9 When they came back from the grave, they told all what they saw to 11 following men and all other people. \v 10 [It was] Meri Magdalin, Joana, Meri the mother of Jems other woman who was with them told to the men with Yesu's authority(apostles). \v 11 But they did not truly approve(believe) their talks, because their talks were to them like mad men might be speaking(nonsence). \v 12 But Fitè immediately got up and went out to the grave. Fitè bent over, [and] saw only cloth put stripped, and he went back wondering what had happened.
\s Walking on the road to Emaus
\p
\v 13 On that same day two [of them] were going from Jerusalem to Emaus about 11kilomitèrs. \v 14 They were talking on the road each other what had happened. \v 15 As they talked and discussed together, Yesu himself came and walked with them. \v 16 But they did not recognize him.
\p
\v 17 He asked them, "Why are you discussing as you walk?"
\p
They stopped walking, with sad face. \v 18 One [of them] name Klofas, asked him, "Are you what kind visiter to Jerusalem and who does not know what have happened in these days?"
\p
\v 19 "Yesu asked, "What happend?" They answered, "About Yesu from Najaret. He was a God's man who make know(prophet) [who was] powerful in talk and did a mirracles in the front of God and all the people. \v 20 The leading sacrifice burning people(high priests) and our rulers handed over him and gave to death, and they nailed him on the cross. \v 21 But we had hope that he would be the one who would save Israil. This is now three day since it was happened. \v 22 Then some women of our group amazed us. They went to the grave early this moning \v 23 but didn't find Yesu's body. They came back to us [and] said to us that they saw men carrying heavenly message(angels), who told them that he was alive. \v 24 Then some from our group went to the grave and found it just as women had said, but they did not see Yesu."
\p
\v 25 He said to them, "How foolish(without thinking) you are, and how hard you saw big mind(faith) in heart all that the God's people who make know(prophets) have spoken! \v 26 Was it necessary for Keriso to suffer after [this] he enter his big light(glory)? \v 27 He began to talk from Moses and all the God's people who make know(prophets), he explained to them what was said in all the God's talks about him.
\p
\v 28 They approached the village where they were going, Yesu was about to pass over. \v 29 But they urged Yesu strongly, "Stay with us because it is nearly evening." So they went in to stay with them.
\p
\v 30 When he sat down in the eating place with them, he took flawè, gave thanks and broke it [and] gave it to them. \v 31 Then their eyes were opened and they recognized who was Yesu, and he disappeared from their eyes. \v 32 They said to each other, "Our hearts were burning in us while he said to us on the road and opened the Buk(scripture)s to us?"
\p
\v 33 They left quickly and returned to Jerusalem. There they found 11 following men and other people gathered together with them \v 34 and said, "It is true! The Lord has risen and has appeared to Saimon." \v 35 Then the two told what had happened to them on the road, and how they recognized Yesu when he broke the flawè.
\s Yesu appeared to his the following men
\p
\v 36 While they were still talking about this, Yesu himself stood among them and said to them "Peace be with you!"
\p
\v 37 This group were full of fear that they thought that they might see a ghost. \v 38 He said to them, "Why are you frightened, and why do doubts in your mind? \v 39 Look at my two hands and my two feet. It is I myself! Touch me and see me; a ghost was not with body(flesh) and bones, as you see I have.
\p
\v 40 When he said about this, he showed his hands and feet. \v 41 They still did not truly approve(believe) it because of Joy and amazement, he asked them "Do you have a piece here to eat?" \v 42 They gave him a piece of roasted fish, \v 43 and he took it and ate it in their eyes.
\p
\v 44 He said to them, "This is what I told you while I was still with you. Every talks must be fulfilled what was written in the laws of Moses, God's people who make know(prophets) and psalms."
\p
\v 45 Then he opened their minds to understand God's talks(Scriptures) what is written. \v 46 He told them, "This is what is written about me. Keriso will be in suffering and rise from the death on the third day, \v 47 and the turning away [from] sin and the washing will be preached in his name to all nations, will begin from Jerusalem. \v 48 You are watching men about these things. \v 49 I am sending you what my father said without-lying saying(did without-lying talk). But you will wait in the city until the power from heaven comes down upon you.
\s The ascension of Yesu
\p
\v 50 When he led them to Betani town, Yesu lifted his hands and blessed them. \v 51 While he was blessing them, he left them and was taken up into heaven. \v 52 Then they worshiped Yesu and returned to Jerusalem with big joy. \v 53 And they kept waiting in the worshipping house every day, and praised God.
